            "content": "# Architecture\n\nFactory is a monorepo of interconnected applications and packages. The core runtime path runs from the CLI through a local daemon to the Factory backend and then to an LLM provider.\n\n## System overview\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    subgraph \"User interfaces\"\n        CLI[\"CLI (droid)\"]\n        Web[\"Web app (apps/web)\"]\n        Desktop[\"Desktop (Electron)\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Local runtime\"\n        Daemon[\"Daemon (factoryd)\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Remote services\"\n        Backend[\"Backend API (Next.js)\"]\n        Relay[\"Relay service\"]\n        Signal[\"Signal (GCP)\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"External\"\n        LLM[\"LLM providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google)\"]\n        GitHub[\"GitHub / Linear / Slack\"]\n        FirestoreDB[\"Firestore\"]\n    end\n\n    CLI -->|\"stdin/stdout JSON-RPC\"| Daemon\n    Web -->|\"WebSocket JSON-RPC\"| Daemon\n    Desktop -->|\"WebSocket JSON-RPC\"| Daemon\n    Daemon -->|\"HTTPS\"| Backend\n    Backend -->|\"streaming\"| LLM\n    Backend -->|\"webhooks / API\"| GitHub\n    Backend -->|\"read/write\"| FirestoreDB\n    Web -->|\"BYOI path via Relay\"| Relay\n    Relay -->|\"WebSocket\"| Daemon\n    Signal -->|\"batch jobs\"| FirestoreDB\n```\n\n## The CLI ↔ daemon ↔ backend chain\n\nThis is the core communication path described in `docs/debugging-daemon.md`:\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant CLI as CLI (apps/cli)\n    participant Daemon as Daemon (apps/daemon)\n    participant Backend as Backend API (apps/backend)\n    participant LLM as LLM provider\n\n    User->>CLI: types a message\n    CLI->>Daemon: JSON-RPC over stdin/stdout\n    Daemon->>Backend: HTTPS request (session update, LLM proxy)\n    Backend->>LLM: streaming request\n    LLM-->>Backend: token stream\n    Backend-->>Daemon: SSE / chunked response\n    Daemon-->>CLI: JSON-RPC events\n    CLI-->>User: rendered TUI output\n```\n\nWhen the web or desktop app is used, the CLI is replaced by a browser client that speaks WebSocket JSON-RPC directly to the daemon.\n\n## Monorepo layout\n\n```\nfactory-mono/\n├── apps/\n│   ├── cli/           # droid CLI (Bun + TypeScript + Ink)\n│   ├── daemon/        # factoryd daemon (Bun + TypeScript)\n│   ├── backend/       # REST API + LLM proxy (Next.js)\n│   ├── web/           # Browser UI (Vite + React)\n│   ├── desktop/       # Electron wrapper\n│   ├── relay/         # WebSocket relay for BYOI\n│   ├── signal/        # Session analytics (GCP Cloud Function)\n│   ├── functions/     # Firebase Cloud Functions\n│   └── factory-vscode-extension/\n├── packages/\n│   ├── droid-core/    # AI agent core (tools, LLMs, streaming)\n│   ├── daemon-core/   # Daemon server + session management\n│   ├── common/        # Shared types, enums, API contracts\n│   ├── frontend/      # Shared React features\n│   ├── core-ui/       # Design system primitives\n│   ├── services/      # Business logic layer\n│   ├── models/        # Data model schemas\n│   ├── logging/       # Logging + error hierarchy\n│   ├── runtime/       # Auth + credentials\n│   └── updater/       # Auto-update utilities\n├── infra/             # Terraform + Ansible\n└── internal/          # Internal tooling and web dashboards\n```\n\n## Key design decisions\n\n**Daemon as local proxy**: The daemon runs locally (or on a CDE) and acts as the bridge between UI clients and the backend. This lets the CLI, web, and desktop share a single agent process without coupling their runtimes together.\n\n**Bun for daemon and CLI**: Both `apps/daemon` and `apps/cli` run on Bun for fast startup and native TypeScript execution without a build step in dev.\n\n**Shared packages**: Logic that appears in both the CLI and the web app lives in `packages/`. The `@factory/droid-core` package owns tool definitions and LLM integration; `@factory/frontend` owns shared React features.\n\n**Turborepo**: All build, test, lint, and typecheck tasks run through Turborepo for caching and parallelism. See `turbo.json` at the repo root.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Apps overview](../apps/index.md) — details on each application\n- [Packages overview](../packages/index.md) — details on each shared package\n- [Systems: JSON-RPC communication](../systems/json-rpc-communication.md) — the wire protocol\n- [Systems: session management](../systems/session-management.md) — session lifecycle\n",
