            "content": "# Getting started\n\nThis page covers how to set up the repo, run the apps in development mode, and run tests.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- **Node.js 18.x** — see `.nvmrc` at the repo root (`nvm use` sets the right version)\n- **npm 11** — specified in `package.json` as `packageManager`\n- **Bun 1.3.10** — required for `apps/cli` and `apps/daemon`\n- **Git** — standard source control\n\nOptional:\n- AWS CLI credentials (for bug report download scripts and infra work)\n- GCP credentials (for `apps/signal` deployment)\n\n## Install\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/Factory-AI/factory-mono.git\ncd factory-mono\nnpm install\n```\n\nThe `postinstall` hook runs `turbo run setup`, which runs each package's `setup` script (including building the CLI alias).\n\n## Run in development\n\n**Do not use `npm run dev` at the root.** It is intentionally disabled. Use one of:\n\n```bash\n# Web stack: backend, web, storybook, admin, daemon\nnpm run dev:web\n\n# Desktop stack: backend, web, storybook, admin, Electron\nnpm run dev:desktop\n```\n\nFor the CLI specifically:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup  # builds droid-dev and droid-localhost shell wrappers\ndroid-dev                     # runs CLI from source against the hosted dev API\ndroid-localhost               # runs CLI from source against a local API\n```\n\n### Dev server logs\n\nEach app writes to a log file while running:\n\n| App     | Log path                       |\n|---------|-------------------------------|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin   | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log`   |\n| desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n| daemon  | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log`  |\n\nUse `tail -f /tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` to stream a log while the app runs.\n\n## Build\n\n```bash\nnpm run build               # build all packages\nnpm run build -- --filter=apps/web   # build one package\n```\n\n## Run tests\n\n```bash\n# CORRECT: pass --filter after --\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common\n\n# Run a single test file (backend)\ncd apps/backend && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts\n\n# Run a single test file (frontend/CLI packages)\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run path/to/file.test.ts\n```\n\n**Warning:** Running `npm run test` without a filter uses ~9 GB of RAM. Always filter when possible.\n\n## Check code quality\n\n```bash\nnpm run fix          # lint + format (preferred over npm run lint)\nnpm run typecheck    # TypeScript checking across all packages\nnpm run knip         # detect unused exports\n```\n\n## Frontend E2E tests\n\n```bash\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e           # headless\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e -- --headed --debug  # visual\n```\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Development workflow](../contributing/development-workflow.md) — branching, PRs, merge\n- [Debugging](../contributing/debugging.md) — daemon and CLI debug guide\n- [Tooling](../contributing/tooling.md) — build system details\n",
