            "content": "# Tooling\n\n## Turborepo\n\n`turbo.json` at the repo root orchestrates all multi-package tasks. Key tasks defined:\n\n| Task | Caching | Notes |\n|------|---------|-------|\n| `build` | yes | Outputs: `.next/**`, `dist/**`, `dist-electron/**` |\n| `typecheck` | no | Run with `npm run typecheck` |\n| `test` | no | Run with `npm run test -- --filter=<pkg>` |\n| `lint` / `fix` | no | `fix` runs lint + format |\n| `setup` | no | Per-package setup scripts |\n| `dev` | no (persistent) | Long-running dev servers |\n\nAlways use `--` before `--filter` when passing flags through npm to Turborepo:\n\n```bash\n# Correct\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/frontend\n\n# Wrong (npm eats --filter, turbo runs everything)\nnpm run test --filter=@factory/frontend\n```\n\n## ESLint\n\nShared config lives in `packages/eslint-config/`. It enforces:\n\n- File organization rules (`enums.ts`, `types.ts`, API types in `@factory/common`)\n- Import ordering and no bare `require()`\n- No direct `process.env` access (use `@factory/environment` instead)\n- UI element bans (`no-restricted-elements` for `div`, `button`, etc.)\n\nRun `npm run fix` to auto-fix lint issues. `npm run lint` to check without fixing.\n\n## Prettier\n\nConfig at `.prettierrc.json`. Run via `npm run format` or as part of `npm run fix`.\n\n## Stylelint\n\nConfig at `.stylelintrc`. Runs via `npm run stylelint`.\n\n## TypeScript\n\nRoot `tsconfig.json` sets base compiler options. Each app/package extends it with a local `tsconfig.json`. Build-time configs are in `tsconfig.build.json` where needed.\n\nRun `npm run typecheck` to check all packages, or `npm run typecheck -- --filter=<pkg>` for one package.\n\n## Knip\n\n`knip.json` at the root detects unused exports and dead code. Run with `npm run knip`. Config excludes generated files and test utilities.\n\n## Husky + pre-commit hooks\n\n`.husky/` contains Git hooks. Pre-commit runs a quick lint check to catch obvious issues before they land in a PR.\n\n## Build system details\n\n- **CLI** — uses `esbuild` (`apps/cli/esbuild.config.js`) to bundle into a single file, then Node.js SEA to create a platform binary.\n- **Daemon** — uses `esbuild` to bundle before running under Bun.\n- **Backend** — Next.js handles its own build via `next build`.\n- **Web** — Vite builds the SPA (`apps/web/vite.config.ts`).\n- **Desktop** — Electron + Vite, with separate main/renderer configs (`apps/desktop/`).\n- **Relay** — `esbuild` bundles the Bun-based WebSocket server.\n- **Signal** — `esbuild` bundles the GCP Cloud Function.\n\n## Code generation\n\nThe `apps/cli/src/generated/` directory contains generated code (e.g., command descriptions). Run the relevant `setup` script to regenerate after changes.\n\n## Infrastructure (Terraform / OpenTofu)\n\nThe `infra/` directory uses OpenTofu (the open-source Terraform fork). Validate with:\n\n```bash\ncd infra && tofu init && tofu validate && tofu fmt\n```\n\nDo not use the `terraform` CLI for infra work in this repo — always use `tofu`.\n",
