            "content": "# Daemon (apps/daemon)\n\n`factoryd` is the background daemon process that runs on the developer's machine (or on a remote CDE). It manages agent sessions, terminal access, and provides the WebSocket server that web/desktop clients connect to.\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe daemon separates the agent runtime from the UI layer. Instead of each UI (CLI, browser, desktop) implementing their own session management, they all connect to a single `factoryd` process through JSON-RPC. This means:\n\n- Sessions persist across UI reconnections\n- Multiple clients can observe the same session\n- The CLI, web, and desktop share identical agent behavior\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/daemon/\n├── src/\n│   ├── index.ts              # Entry point\n│   ├── environment.ts        # Environment variable loading\n│   ├── constants.ts          # Default ports and config\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   └── UpdateService.ts  # Auto-update logic\n│   ├── telemetry/\n│   │   └── DaemonOtelTracingClient.ts\n│   └── utils/\n│       ├── command-wrapper.ts\n│       ├── daemon-telemetry-client.ts\n│       ├── exit-with-code.ts\n│       └── parent-health-monitor.ts\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/index.ts` | Entry point — env loading, telemetry, auto-update, CLI arg parsing, starts `DaemonCore` |\n| `src/environment.ts` | Reads `.env` files and exposes typed config |\n| `src/services/UpdateService.ts` | Checks for and applies daemon binary updates |\n| `src/utils/parent-health-monitor.ts` | Monitors the parent process (Electron or CLI) and exits if it dies |\n\n## Startup sequence\n\n1. Load `.env` files from the daemon app directory.\n2. Initialize telemetry (`DaemonTelemetryClient`).\n3. Initialize OpenTelemetry tracing (if `FACTORY_OTEL_ENABLED=true`).\n4. Run auto-update check (skipped if `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=true`).\n5. Parse CLI arguments with Commander.\n6. Build `DaemonCoreConfig` and instantiate `DaemonCore` from `@factory/daemon-core`.\n7. Monitor parent process health.\n8. Start the WebSocket server.\n\n## Ports\n\n| Environment | Port |\n|-------------|------|\n| Production | 37643 |\n| Development | 41723 |\n\n## Relationship to daemon-core\n\n`apps/daemon` is a thin wrapper. The actual daemon logic (WebSocket server, session management, terminal PTY, request handlers) lives in `packages/daemon-core`. This separation lets `apps/cli` also run a daemon inline when needed, without duplicating the core implementation.\n\n## Auto-update\n\nThe daemon checks for updates at startup via `apps/daemon/src/services/UpdateService.ts`, which uses the `@factory/updater` package. When running inside the Electron bundle, `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=true` prevents the daemon from overwriting itself (Electron manages its own updates).\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [daemon-core package](../packages/daemon-core.md) — the actual daemon implementation\n- [Systems: session management](../systems/session-management.md) — session lifecycle\n- [Systems: JSON-RPC communication](../systems/json-rpc-communication.md) — the wire protocol\n- [Desktop app](./desktop.md) — the Electron app that bundles the daemon\n",
