            "content": "# Backend API (apps/backend)\n\nThe backend is a Next.js 15 application running on port 3000. It provides REST API endpoints for auth, sessions, billing, LLM proxying, integrations, and cron jobs. The Next.js web frontend in this app is deprecated — the active UI is `apps/web`.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/backend/src/\n├── app/              # Next.js App Router pages and API routes\n├── api/              # Legacy API helpers\n├── constants.ts      # App-wide constants\n├── env/              # Environment variable validation\n├── features/         # Feature-specific modules (feature flags, etc.)\n├── instrumentation.ts # OpenTelemetry setup\n├── middleware.ts     # Next.js middleware (auth, CORS)\n├── routes.ts         # Route configuration\n├── services/         # Business logic and external integrations\n│   ├── billing/      # Orb billing integration\n│   ├── bigquery/     # BigQuery analytics writes\n│   ├── computer/     # Computer use / BYOI sessions\n│   ├── e2b/          # E2B sandbox management\n│   ├── integrations/ # GitHub, Linear, Slack, etc.\n│   ├── orb/          # Subscription and usage management\n│   ├── segment/      # Analytics (Segment)\n│   ├── stripe/       # Stripe payment processing\n│   ├── workos/       # WorkOS auth integration\n│   └── ...\n├── types/            # Shared TypeScript types for this app\n└── utils/            # Backend utility functions\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/middleware.ts` | Validates JWT tokens, applies CORS, attaches user context to requests |\n| `src/instrumentation.ts` | Initializes Sentry and OTEL tracing |\n| `src/routes.ts` | Maps URL patterns to handlers |\n| `src/features/feature-flags/` | Server-side Statsig feature flag evaluation |\n| `src/services/workos/` | WorkOS auth, user management, JWT issuance |\n| `src/services/billing/` | Orb billing, usage tracking, subscription management |\n| `src/services/integrations/` | GitHub app, Linear, Slack webhook handlers |\n\n## LLM proxying\n\nThe backend proxies LLM requests from daemons and CLI clients to Anthropic, OpenAI, and Google. The proxy adds authentication, rate limiting, usage tracking, and error normalization before forwarding to the upstream provider.\n\nLLM proxy endpoints live under `src/app/api/llm/`. See [API: LLM proxy](./api-routes.md#llm-proxy) for details.\n\n## Authentication\n\nAuth is handled by WorkOS. The middleware at `src/middleware.ts` validates WorkOS JWTs on every request. API keys are also supported for programmatic access.\n\n## Cron jobs\n\nNext.js Route Handlers with `GET` exports serve as cron endpoints, triggered by external schedulers (Vercel Cron or similar). These handle periodic tasks like usage rollups, subscription syncs, and cleanup.\n\n## External integrations\n\nThe `src/services/integrations/` directory contains clients for:\n- GitHub (app installation, webhooks, repository access)\n- Linear (issue creation, ticket linking)\n- Slack (workspace integration, notifications)\n- WorkOS (auth and directory sync)\n- Stripe and Orb (billing)\n- Segment (analytics)\n- E2B (sandbox environments)\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [API routes](./api-routes.md) — REST endpoint reference\n- [Security](../../security.md) — auth, authorization, API key handling\n",
