            "content": "# API routes\n\nThe backend exposes REST endpoints organized by domain. All routes live under `apps/backend/src/app/api/`.\n\n## Route categories\n\n### Auth\n\n| Method | Path | Purpose |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| `POST` | `/api/auth/callback` | WorkOS OAuth callback handler |\n| `GET` | `/api/auth/session` | Get current session info |\n| `POST` | `/api/auth/logout` | Invalidate session |\n\n### Sessions\n\n| Method | Path | Purpose |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| `POST` | `/api/sessions` | Create a new Droid session |\n| `GET` | `/api/sessions/:id` | Get session by ID |\n| `PATCH` | `/api/sessions/:id` | Update session (title, tags, etc.) |\n| `DELETE` | `/api/sessions/:id` | Delete a session |\n| `GET` | `/api/sessions` | List sessions for the current user |\n\n### LLM proxy\n\nThe LLM proxy is one of the most performance-critical parts of the backend. It streams tokens from upstream providers back to the daemon.\n\n| Method | Path | Purpose |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| `POST` | `/api/llm/stream` | Streaming LLM request (SSE) |\n| `POST` | `/api/llm/complete` | Non-streaming LLM completion |\n\nThe proxy adds:\n- Request authentication and user context\n- Usage recording for billing\n- Provider-specific error normalization\n- Rate limiting\n\n### Integrations\n\n| Method | Path | Purpose |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| `POST` | `/api/integrations/github/webhook` | GitHub webhook receiver |\n| `GET` | `/api/integrations/github/install` | GitHub App installation flow |\n| `POST` | `/api/integrations/linear/webhook` | Linear webhook receiver |\n| `POST` | `/api/integrations/slack/webhook` | Slack event receiver |\n\n### Billing\n\n| Method | Path | Purpose |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| `GET` | `/api/billing/usage` | Current usage summary |\n| `GET` | `/api/billing/subscription` | Subscription status |\n| `POST` | `/api/billing/checkout` | Start checkout session |\n\n### Settings and org management\n\n| Method | Path | Purpose |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| `GET` | `/api/settings` | Get user/org settings |\n| `PATCH` | `/api/settings` | Update settings |\n| `GET` | `/api/org` | Get organization details |\n| `POST` | `/api/org/members` | Invite member |\n\n### Wiki\n\n| Method | Path | Purpose |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| `POST` | `/api/wiki/pages` | Upload wiki pages |\n| `GET` | `/api/wiki/:repoUrl` | Get wiki for a repository |\n\n## API type contracts\n\nAll request and response types are defined in `packages/common/src/api/`. Each service has its own subdirectory:\n\n```\npackages/common/src/api/\n├── session/types.ts\n├── llm/types.ts\n├── billing/types.ts\n├── integrations/types.ts\n└── ...\n```\n\nWhen adding a new endpoint, define its types in `@factory/common` first — not inline in the backend. This is enforced by ESLint.\n\n## Error responses\n\nThe backend uses typed error classes from `@factory/logging/errors`. HTTP error codes map directly to classes:\n\n| Class | HTTP Status |\n|-------|------------|\n| `ResponseError400BadRequest` | 400 |\n| `ResponseError401Unauthorized` | 401 |\n| `ResponseError403Forbidden` | 403 |\n| `ResponseError404NotFound` | 404 |\n| `ResponseError429RateLimitExceeded` | 429 |\n\nSee `docs/error-handling.md` for the full error handling guide.\n",
