            "content": "# Relay (apps/relay)\n\nThe relay is a WebSocket multiplexer that lets browser clients connect to daemons running on remote machines they cannot reach directly. This is the core infrastructure for the BYOI (Bring Your Own Infrastructure) and BYOK (Bring Your Own Keys) modes.\n\n## Architecture\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    Browser -->|\"WS client\"| Relay\n    Relay -->|\"WS agent\"| Daemon\n    Relay --- ChannelSession\n    ChannelSession --- ChannelRegistry\n```\n\n- **RelayServer** — Bun HTTP + WebSocket server. Handles the upgrade routing and frame normalization.\n- **ChannelSession** — per-computer multiplexer: wraps client frames in envelopes, decodes computer envelopes and routes to the target client.\n- **ChannelRegistry** — in-memory lookup of active sessions by `computerId`.\n\n## Routes\n\n| Endpoint | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `WS /v0/computer/:computerId/agent` | Daemon connects here (one per channel) |\n| `WS /v0/computer/:computerId/client` | Browser clients connect here (N per channel) |\n| `GET /health` | Health check (returns 200) |\n\nClients are rejected with 503 if the daemon is not connected. `computerId` must be a valid UUID.\n\n## How it works\n\n1. The daemon connects to `/v0/computer/:computerId/agent` and registers itself.\n2. Browser clients connect to `/v0/computer/:computerId/client`.\n3. The relay maintains a `ChannelSession` per `computerId` that buffers and forwards messages between all connected clients and the single daemon.\n4. When the daemon disconnects, all client connections are closed.\n\n## Envelope protocol\n\nThe relay uses an envelope protocol defined in `packages/common/src/relay`. Codec functions live in `packages/utils/src/relay`. Clients and daemons wrap their JSON-RPC messages in envelopes before sending, and the relay strips/adds envelopes when routing.\n\n## Configuration\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_PORT` | `8080` | Port to listen on |\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_HOST` | `0.0.0.0` | Host to bind |\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_DEBUG` | `false` | Enable debug logging |\n\n## Testing\n\n```bash\n# All tests (unit + integration)\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/relay\n\n# E2E smoke test (spawns real relay + mock computer + mock clients)\ncd apps/relay && bun scripts/smoke.ts\n```\n\nUnit tests mock WebSocket sockets. Integration tests use real connections. The smoke test runs the full relay path across process boundaries.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Web app](./web.md) — the browser client that connects via the relay\n- [Daemon](./daemon.md) — the daemon that connects as the \"computer\" endpoint\n",
