            "content": "# Signal (apps/signal)\n\nSignal is a GCP Cloud Function that processes Factory chat sessions to identify friction and delight moments. Results go to BigQuery, with daily summaries in Slack and friction patterns converted to Linear tickets.\n\n## Purpose\n\nSignal gives the Factory team visibility into how users experience Droid. It runs OpenAI's Batch API against historical sessions to detect things like repeated rephrasing (friction) or \"that works!\" moments (delight).\n\n## Architecture\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    CloudScheduler[\"Cloud Scheduler\"] -->|\"trigger\"| CloudFunction[\"Cloud Function\"]\n    CloudFunction -->|\"submit/poll batches\"| OpenAI[\"OpenAI Batch API\"]\n    CloudFunction -->|\"write results\"| BigQuery[\"BigQuery\"]\n    CloudFunction -->|\"daily report\"| Slack[\"Slack\"]\n    CloudFunction -->|\"create tickets\"| Linear[\"Linear (via Droid)\"]\n    BigQuery -->|\"read sessions\"| CloudFunction\n```\n\n## Operating modes\n\nThe function supports four modes, triggered by the Cloud Scheduler:\n\n| Mode | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `submit_batch` | Stream sessions from BigQuery and submit to OpenAI Batch API |\n| `process_results` | Poll completed batches and insert results to BigQuery |\n| `daily_report` | Query aggregated stats and send a Slack summary |\n| `analyze_and_ticket` | Run Droid to analyze friction patterns and create Linear tickets |\n\n## Signal types\n\n**Friction** — detects obstacles:\n- Error events (model errors, tool failures, timeouts)\n- Repeated rephrasing (≥3 consecutive messages restating the same request)\n- Escalation tone (words like \"broken\", \"frustrating\")\n- Platform confusion (user asks how to use Factory features)\n- Abandoned tool flows\n- Backtracking (undo, revert, deletes generated code)\n- Context churn (adding/removing the same file repeatedly)\n\n**Delight** — identifies positive moments:\n- Positive exclamations (🙌, 🎉, \"awesome\", \"perfect\")\n- First-attempt success (task done in ≤2 turns with thanks)\n- Rapid tool confirmation\n- Adoption milestones (first use of an advanced feature)\n- Efficiency gain mentions (\"saved me hours\")\n\n**Facets** — session metadata:\n- LLM-derived: language, intent category, task description, outcome\n- Structured: turn count, duration, tool call count, context objects added\n- From OTEL: programming languages (via file extensions)\n\n## BigQuery output tables\n\n| Table | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| `friction_session_results` | Friction events with severity and citations |\n| `delight_session_results` | Delight moments with confidence and citations |\n| `session_facets` | Session metadata (intents, tech stack, outcomes) |\n| `batch_summaries` | Processing state tracking |\n\n## Related packages\n\n`packages/signal-core` contains shared signal definitions (prompts, schemas, mappers) used by both `apps/signal` and `apps/admin`. Moving shared logic there prevents duplication.\n\n## Deployment\n\nSignal deploys to GCP automatically on push to `dev` via `.github/workflows/signal-deploy.yml`. See `apps/signal/DEPLOY.md` for manual deployment and secrets setup.\n\nSkills in `apps/signal/.factory/skills/` are bundled at deploy time by `apps/signal/deploy.sh`.\n",
