            "content": "# Packages\n\nThe monorepo has 22 shared packages under `packages/`. They fall into three groups:\n\n## Core packages\n\nThese are the most important packages that every contributor encounters:\n\n| Package | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| [`@factory/droid-core`](./droid-core/index.md) | AI agent — tool definitions, LLM integration, streaming |\n| [`@factory/daemon-core`](./daemon-core.md) | Daemon server, session management, terminal (PTY) |\n| [`@factory/frontend`](./frontend.md) | Shared React features for web and desktop |\n| [`@factory/core-ui`](./core-ui.md) | Design system primitives (mandatory for UI) |\n| [`@factory/common`](./common.md) | Shared constants, enums, API type contracts |\n\n## Utility packages\n\n| Package | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `@factory/services` | Business logic and external service integrations |\n| `@factory/models` | TypeScript type definitions and data model schemas |\n| `@factory/logging` | Logging utilities, error hierarchy, `MetaError` |\n| `@factory/utils` | Shared utility functions |\n| `@factory/runtime` | Auth, credentials, and keytar integration |\n| `@factory/updater` | Auto-update version checking and installation |\n| `@factory/environment` | Strongly-typed environment variable access |\n| `@factory/signal-core` | Signal analytics prompts and schemas |\n| `@factory/daemon-client` | Client library for talking to the daemon |\n| `@factory/mcp` | Model Context Protocol utilities |\n\n## Development packages\n\n| Package | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `@factory/eslint-config` | Shared ESLint rules (enforces file organization, import style, etc.) |\n| `@factory/test-utils` | Shared test helpers and mock factories |\n| `@factory/component-library` | Legacy component library (being migrated to `@factory/core-ui`) |\n\n## Dependency rules\n\n- `@factory/common` has no internal dependencies — it can be imported everywhere\n- `@factory/core-ui` has no internal dependencies beyond `@factory/common`\n- `@factory/droid-core` imports `@factory/common` and `@factory/logging`\n- Application code (`apps/*`) can import any package\n- Packages must not import from `apps/*`\n",
