            "content": "# common package\n\n`@factory/common` contains shared constants, enums, and TypeScript type definitions used across all apps and packages. It has no internal Factory dependencies, so it can be safely imported anywhere in the monorepo.\n\n## Purpose\n\nA single source of truth for:\n- API request/response type contracts between the frontend, backend, and CLI\n- Feature flag definitions\n- Shared enum values (session states, tool names, error codes)\n- Daemon communication constants\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/common/src/\n├── api/              # API type contracts organized by service\n│   ├── session/      # Session CRUD types\n│   ├── llm/          # LLM request/response types\n│   ├── billing/      # Billing and subscription types\n│   ├── daemon/       # Daemon config and protocol types\n│   ├── integrations/ # GitHub, Linear, Slack types\n│   ├── relay/        # Relay envelope protocol types\n│   ├── wiki/         # Wiki page and metadata types\n│   └── ...\n├── agent/            # Agent readiness and config types\n├── automations/      # Automation type definitions\n├── billing/          # Billing enums\n├── cli/              # CLI-specific shared types\n├── daemon/           # Daemon config constants\n├── droid/            # Droid configuration types\n├── events/           # Event type definitions\n├── feature-flags/\n│   └── constants.ts  # All Statsig feature flag definitions\n├── integrations/     # Integration type definitions\n├── llm/              # LLM model enums and constants\n├── organization/     # Org and team types\n├── relay/            # Relay envelope protocol definitions\n├── repositories/     # Repository type definitions\n├── session/          # Session types and enums\n├── settings/         # Settings type definitions\n├── shared/           # Cross-cutting shared types\n└── ...\n```\n\n## API type convention\n\nAll API contracts live in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts`. This is enforced by ESLint — you cannot define API types inline in `apps/backend` or `packages/frontend`.\n\nWhen adding a new endpoint:\n1. Define request/response types in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts`\n2. Import them in both the backend handler and the frontend API client\n\n```ts\n// packages/common/src/api/session/types.ts\nexport interface CreateSessionRequest {\n  repoUrl: string;\n  title?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface CreateSessionResponse {\n  sessionId: string;\n  createdAt: string;\n}\n```\n\n## Feature flags\n\nAll feature flags are defined in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`:\n\n```ts\nexport const FactoryFeatureFlags = {\n  WikiDashboard: {\n    displayName: 'Wiki Dashboard',\n    statsigName: 'wiki_dashboard',\n    defaultValue: false,\n  },\n  // ...\n};\n```\n\nAdd a flag here after creating it in the Statsig console.\n\n## Daemon constants\n\n`packages/common/src/daemon/` exports the WebSocket server config (ports, connection timeouts) and machine type enums used by both `apps/daemon` and `packages/daemon-core`.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Backend API routes](../apps/backend/api-routes.md) — consumes these types\n- [frontend package](./frontend.md) — consumes these types\n- [Contributing: patterns](../contributing/patterns-and-conventions.md) — type conventions\n",
