            "content": "# CI/CD\n\nAll CI/CD is managed through GitHub Actions. Workflows live in `.github/workflows/`.\n\n## PR checks (run on every PR)\n\n| Workflow | File | What it checks |\n|----------|------|----------------|\n| Basic checks | `basic-checks.yml` | Fast sanity checks |\n| ESLint | `eslint.yml` | Lint errors |\n| Format | `format.yml` | Prettier formatting |\n| TypeScript | `typecheck.yml` | Type errors across all packages |\n| Tests | `test.yml` | Unit tests |\n| Backend tests | `test-backend.yml` | Backend-specific tests |\n| CLI tests | `test-cli.yml` | CLI unit tests |\n| Knip | `knip.yml` | Unused exports |\n| PR conventions | `pr-conventions.yml` | Conventional Commits title, Linear ticket in body |\n| Package lock | `package-lock-check.yml` | `package-lock.json` consistency |\n| OpenAPI validate | `openapi-validate.yml` | OpenAPI spec validation |\n| Affected check | `check-affected.yml` | Determines which packages are affected by the PR |\n| Semantic diff | `semantic-diff.yml` | LLM-powered change analysis |\n\n## Deployment workflows\n\n### Backend and web (Vercel)\n\n| Workflow | Trigger | Target |\n|----------|---------|--------|\n| `deploy-dev-web.yml` | Push to `dev` | Vercel preview |\n| `deploy-prod.yml` | Release tag | Vercel production |\n| `deploy-prod-admin.yml` | Release tag | Admin app |\n| `deploy-prod-app.yml` | Release tag | Main app |\n\n### CLI and daemon (S3)\n\n| Workflow | Trigger | What it does |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `cli-release.yml` | Release tag | Builds CLI SEA binaries for all platforms, uploads to S3 |\n| `cli-release-npm.yml` | Release tag | Publishes CLI to npm |\n| `factoryd-release.yml` | Release tag | Builds and uploads daemon binaries to S3 |\n| `cli-auto-update-test.yml` | Scheduled | Tests the auto-update path |\n\n### Desktop (Electron)\n\n`desktop-release.yml` — builds Electron apps for macOS, Windows, and Linux and uploads them to S3 for distribution and auto-update.\n\n### Relay (AWS)\n\n`deploy-relay-aws.yml` — deploys the relay service to AWS infrastructure (ECS or Lambda). Uses OpenTofu for infrastructure changes.\n\n### Signal (GCP)\n\n`signal-deploy.yml` and `signal-build.yml` — build and deploy the GCP Cloud Function. Skills from `apps/signal/.factory/skills/` are bundled at deploy time.\n\n### Infrastructure (OpenTofu)\n\n`opentofu.yml` — runs `tofu plan` on pull requests and `tofu apply` on merges to `dev` or `main` for infrastructure changes in `infra/`.\n\n## Lint healing\n\n`lint-format-with-healing.yml` — runs after a PR merge and auto-commits lint/format fixes if the CI passes but formatting drifts.\n\n## Droid review automation\n\n`droid-review.yml` — an automated Droid agent that reviews PRs and posts comments.\n\n## Eval workflows\n\n`submit-eval.yml` and `manual-eval-trigger.yml` — trigger benchmark eval runs against the CLI.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Release process](./release-process.md) — version bumps and distribution\n- [Infrastructure](./ci-cd.md) — OpenTofu configuration\n",
