          "input": {
            "content": "# Factory platform overview\n\nFactory is an AI software engineering platform built around Droid, an AI agent that runs in the terminal and helps developers write, review, and ship code. The platform combines a local CLI tool, a background daemon, a web/desktop interface, and a backend API into a single system where developers interact with an AI agent through a chat-like session model.\n\n## What the platform does\n\nDroid accepts natural language instructions and executes them autonomously using a set of tools: reading and editing files, running shell commands, searching codebases, browsing the web, and interacting with third-party services. It can operate interactively (the developer watches the agent work in a TUI) or non-interactively (headless exec mode, suitable for CI pipelines).\n\nThe platform supports two interaction modes:\n\n- **Interactive sessions** — the developer has a continuous conversation with the agent, confirming tool use, redirecting the agent mid-task, and reviewing results\n- **Missions** (AGI mode) — the agent decomposes large tasks into features, spawns parallel worker sessions, and tracks progress toward a goal without continuous human oversight\n\n## Who uses it\n\nDroid targets software engineers who want to delegate implementation work to an AI agent while staying in the loop through a TUI or web interface. The platform includes both a local installation path (desktop app, CLI) and a cloud-based path (web app connecting to remote cloud development environments).\n\n## Key components\n\n| Component | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli` | The Droid CLI — interactive TUI and headless exec mode |\n| `apps/daemon` | `factoryd` — background process managing droid sessions |\n| `apps/web` | Web interface for browser-based Droid sessions |\n| `apps/desktop` | Electron desktop app bundling the web UI and daemon |\n| `apps/backend` | Next.js API service — auth, billing, LLM proxy, integrations |\n| `apps/admin` | Admin dashboard for platform management |\n| `packages/droid-core` | AI agent core — tools, LLM providers, streaming |\n| `packages/core-ui` | Design system used by all web UIs |\n| `packages/frontend` | Shared React features (sessions, settings, analytics) |\n| `packages/common` | Shared types, enums, and API contracts |\n| `packages/daemon-core` | Core daemon logic — WebSocket server, session management |\n\n## Quick links\n\n- [System architecture](architecture.md)\n- [Getting started](getting-started.md)\n- [Project glossary](glossary.md)\n- [How to contribute](../how-to-contribute/index.md)\n- [Apps overview](../apps/index.md)\n- [Packages overview](../packages/index.md)\n",
            "file_path": "/Users/jonathanlucuix-andre/Documents/test-repos/factory-mono/droid-wiki/overview/index.md"
          },
