            "content": "# How to contribute\n\nThis section covers the practical mechanics of working in the factory-mono codebase: branching strategy, PR conventions, testing requirements, and the tools used across the development lifecycle.\n\n## Before you start\n\nRead the `AGENTS.md` file at the repo root. It contains the commands, architecture overview, and rules that all contributors (human and AI) follow. Pay attention to:\n\n- The `--filter` syntax for running turbo commands on specific packages\n- The prohibition on `npm run dev` at the root (use `dev:web` or `dev:desktop`)\n- The requirement to use `@factory/core-ui` components, never raw HTML elements\n\n## Work pickup\n\n1. Pick a Linear ticket from the team backlog\n2. Create a branch from `dev` (not `main`): `git checkout -b my-feature dev`\n3. Keep branches short-lived; rebase against `dev` if they age\n\n## PR process\n\n- **Title format**: `type(scope): description` — e.g., `feat(cli): add wiki-upload command`\n  - Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`\n  - Scope: the workspace name (`cli`, `backend`, `frontend`, `monorepo`, etc.)\n- **Description**: must include the Linear ticket (e.g., `Closes FAC-1234`)\n- **Template**: see `.github/pull_request_template.md`\n- PRs merge into `dev`; `main` is the release branch\n\n## Definition of done\n\nBefore marking a PR ready for review:\n\n- All new code has unit tests (see [testing guide](testing.md))\n- `npm run typecheck -- --filter=<your-package>` passes\n- `npm run fix -- --filter=<your-package>` passes (lint + format)\n- No unused exports (`npm run knip`)\n- For UI changes: reviewed against the Figma design\n\n## Code organization rules\n\nESLint enforces these automatically, but knowing them avoids surprises:\n\n- Enums go in `enums.ts`, types go in `types.ts` within each package\n- API types go in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts`\n- Use absolute imports (`@factory/...`, `@/...`), never relative `../../`\n- No `require()` — use ES6 `import`\n- No raw HTML elements in UI code — use `Box`, `Button`, `Input`, `Text` from `@factory/core-ui`\n\n## See also\n\n- [Development workflow](development-workflow.md)\n- [Testing](testing.md)\n- [Debugging](debugging.md)\n- [Patterns and conventions](patterns-and-conventions.md)\n- [Tooling](tooling.md)\n",
