            "content": "# Development workflow\n\n## Branch strategy\n\nAll feature work branches from `dev`. The `main` branch is for releases only and should not be the base for regular PRs.\n\n```bash\ngit checkout dev\ngit pull\ngit checkout -b feat/fac-1234-my-feature\n```\n\n## Dev server startup\n\nStart the full web stack (backend + web + admin + storybook + daemon):\n\n```bash\nnpm run dev:web\n```\n\nFor desktop development:\n\n```bash\nnpm run dev:desktop\n```\n\nBoth commands stream output to the console and write to log files under `/tmp/`. Check logs for errors:\n\n```bash\ntail -f /tmp/factory-dev-backend.log\ntail -f /tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log\n```\n\n## CLI development\n\nThe CLI uses `tsx` in dev mode so changes take effect immediately without a build step. After starting the dev stack, set up the alias:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup\nsource ~/.zshrc   # or open a new terminal\ndroid-dev         # runs CLI against hosted dev environment\ndroid-localhost   # runs CLI against local API\n```\n\nWhen you change CLI or daemon source code:\n\n1. If you changed `apps/cli`: `cd apps/cli && npm run setup` to rebuild\n2. If you changed `apps/daemon` or `packages/daemon-core`: restart the daemon process\n3. Start a new session — old sessions won't pick up code changes\n\n## Making changes\n\nFor UI changes in `apps/web`, `apps/desktop`, or `packages/frontend`:\n\n- Components must use `@factory/core-ui` primitives. Never use `<div>`, `<button>`, or `<input>` directly\n- Colors come from `colors.semantics`, never hardcoded hex values\n- See [patterns and conventions](patterns-and-conventions.md) for Redux state selection rules\n\nFor API changes in `apps/backend`:\n\n- Define request/response types in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts` first\n- Use `handleRouteMiddleware` for all route handlers — never craft `NextResponse` manually on errors\n- Use `MetaError` or a `ResponseErrorXXX` class; never throw vanilla `Error`\n\nFor changes to `packages/droid-core`:\n\n- Tool definitions live in `packages/droid-core/src/tools/definitions/`\n- LLM provider adapters live in `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/`\n- All three provider families (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google) need to handle new capabilities consistently\n\n## Before pushing\n\nRun the checks targeted to your package:\n\n```bash\nnpm run typecheck -- --filter=<package>\nnpm run fix -- --filter=<package>\n```\n\nDo not run `npm run test` without a `--filter` unless you need the full suite — it uses ~9 GB of RAM.\n\n## Pull request review\n\nAssign at least one reviewer. For UI changes, get design sign-off. PRs with failing CI checks should not be merged. The CI runs:\n\n- `typecheck`\n- `lint` / `fix`\n- `test`\n- Playwright E2E (critical paths)\n- `knip` (unused exports)\n- PR title convention check\n\nSee [tooling](tooling.md) for details on what each CI workflow does.\n",
