            "content": "# Debugging\n\n## Log file locations\n\n| Environment | Directory | Key files |\n|---|---|---|\n| Production | `~/.factory/logs/` | `factoryd.log`, `droid-log-single.log`, `console.log` |\n| Development | `~/.factory-dev/logs/` | Same files, dev builds |\n\nUse the dev directory when working against local or hosted-dev builds. Production logs are from installed releases.\n\n## Dev server logs\n\nWhen running `npm run dev:web` or `npm run dev:desktop`, each app writes to a dedicated log file:\n\n```bash\ntail -f /tmp/factory-dev-backend.log   # backend API\ntail -f /tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log    # factoryd\ntail -f /tmp/factory-dev-admin.log     # admin dashboard\n```\n\n## Tracing a message through the stack\n\nThe communication path for a user message is:\n\n```\nFrontend (DaemonSessionController.ts)\n    ↓ WebSocket JSON-RPC\nDaemon (droid-request-handler.ts)\n    ↓ stdin/stdout JSON-RPC\nCLI (streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.tsx)\n```\n\nKey files for tracing each layer:\n\n| Layer | Key file |\n|---|---|\n| Protocol | `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`, `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/` |\n| CLI | `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` |\n| Daemon | `apps/daemon/src/server/handlers/droid-request-handler.ts` |\n| Frontend | `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` |\n\n```bash\n# Check if CLI emitted the event\ngrep \"your-feature\" ~/.factory-dev/logs/droid-log-single.log\n\n# Check if daemon received/forwarded it\ngrep \"your-feature\" ~/.factory-dev/logs/factoryd.log\n\n# Watch all dev logs live\ntail -f ~/.factory-dev/logs/*.log\n```\n\n## Common issues\n\n### Changes not taking effect\n\n1. Rebuild CLI: `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`\n2. Kill and restart the daemon process\n3. Start a **new** session — old sessions won't pick up code changes\n4. Verify you're checking `~/.factory-dev/` not `~/.factory/`\n\n### Schema or enum mismatch\n\nIf the CLI sends a notification but the frontend doesn't receive it:\n\n1. Check that the notification type is in `SessionNotificationType` (`packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`)\n2. Check that the schema is defined in `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/cli.ts`\n3. Check that a handler exists in `DaemonSessionController.ts`\n\n### Timing issues\n\nNotifications sent before the session is registered with the daemon are silently dropped. Always emit notifications after session initialization completes — never during startup.\n\n## Adding debug logging\n\n```typescript\nimport { logInfo } from '@factory/logging';\n\nlogInfo('[MyFeature] Event received', { count: items.length });\n```\n\nUse `logInfo` for breadcrumbs, `logWarn` for unexpected-but-handled conditions. Never call `logError` — it's removed from the codebase. See [patterns and conventions](patterns-and-conventions.md) for the full error and logging rules.\n\n## Daemon debugging guide\n\nSee `docs/debugging-daemon.md` for the full daemon/CLI/frontend communication debugging runbook including:\n\n- How to attach a Node inspector to the daemon\n- How to replay a failed session from logs\n- How to diagnose WebSocket connection failures\n",
