            "content": "# Patterns and conventions\n\n## Error handling\n\nThe codebase has strict rules for errors. Full details are in `docs/error-handling.md`. The short version:\n\n**Never throw vanilla `Error`:**\n```typescript\n// Wrong\nthrow new Error('Something failed');\n\n// Right\nthrow new MetaError('Something failed', { contextId, reason });\n```\n\n**Use typed HTTP errors for API routes:**\n```typescript\nimport {\n  ResponseError404NotFound,\n  ResponseError403Forbidden,\n} from '@factory/logging/errors';\n\nif (!resource) throw new ResponseError404NotFound('Resource not found');\nif (!hasPermission) throw new ResponseError403Forbidden('Access denied');\n```\n\n**Bubble by default — don't wrap unless you have a reason:**\n```typescript\n// Wrong — pointless try/catch\ntry {\n  return await callService();\n} catch (error) {\n  logWarn('Service call failed', { id });\n  throw error;  // just re-throws with no value added\n}\n\n// Right — breadcrumb only\nlogInfo('Calling service', { id });\nreturn await callService();\n```\n\n**`logException` means you've handled the error; never `logException` and rethrow:**\n```typescript\n// Wrong\ntry {\n  doThing();\n} catch (error) {\n  logException(error, 'doThing failed');\n  throw error;  // duplicates Sentry issues\n}\n\n// Right — logException only when swallowing\ntry {\n  doThing();\n} catch (error) {\n  logException(error, 'doThing failed, using fallback');\n  return fallbackValue;\n}\n```\n\n## Logging\n\n```typescript\nimport { logInfo, logWarn, logException } from '@factory/logging';\n\nlogInfo('Processing request', { userId, action });  // breadcrumbs\nlogWarn('Rate limit approaching', { usage: 950, limit: 1000 });  // potential issues\n```\n\n**No `logError`** — it does not exist in this codebase.\n\n## Redux state selection\n\nSelect precisely to avoid unnecessary re-renders:\n\n```typescript\n// Wrong — selects the whole slice\nconst { messageTree } = useSelector((state: RootState) => state.assembly);\n\n// Right — selects only what's needed\nconst messageTree = useSelector((state: RootState) => state.assembly.messageTree);\n```\n\n## UI components\n\nAll UI must use `@factory/core-ui` primitives. The linter enforces this.\n\n```typescript\n// Wrong\n<div className=\"container\"><button onClick={handler}>Click</button></div>\n\n// Right\n<Box><Button onClick={handler}>Click</Button></Box>\n```\n\nColors come from the semantic token system, never hardcoded:\n\n```typescript\n// Wrong\ncolor: '#FF5733'\n\n// Right\ncolor: colors.semantics.actionPrimary\n```\n\n## Environment variables\n\nRead environment variables through `@factory/environment`, not `process.env`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { EnvironmentVariable } from '@factory/environment';\nconst apiKey = EnvironmentVariable.FACTORY_API_KEY;\n```\n\nThe `no-direct-process-env` ESLint rule enforces this. For migrating existing `process.env` usage, see the `process-env-migration` skill.\n\n## API type definitions\n\nEvery new API endpoint needs its request and response types defined in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts` before implementation. This ensures the frontend and backend share the same contract.\n\n```typescript\n// packages/common/src/api/sessions/types.ts\nexport interface CreateSessionRequest {\n  repoUrl: string;\n  title?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface CreateSessionResponse {\n  sessionId: string;\n  createdAt: string;\n}\n```\n\n## Feature flags\n\nFeature flags are checked via the `FactoryFeatureFlags` constants defined in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`.\n\n**Frontend:**\n```typescript\nconst isEnabled = useFeatureFlagValue(FactoryFeatureFlags.MyFeature);\n```\n\n**Backend:**\n```typescript\nconst featureFlags = await getFeatureFlagInstance();\nconst isEnabled = await featureFlags.checkFlag(FactoryFeatureFlags.MyFeature, orgId);\n```\n\nAlways provide a fallback — feature flag checks can fail gracefully. See `docs/feature-flags.md` for details.\n\n## Metrics\n\n```typescript\nimport { Metrics } from '@factory/logging';\n\nMetrics.addToCounter('session_created_count', 1, { source: 'web' });\nMetrics.recordHistogram('request_latency_ms', duration, { endpoint: '/api/sessions' });\nMetrics.setGauge('active_sessions_count', count);\n```\n\nInclude the unit in histogram metric names (`_ms`, `_bytes`). See `docs/metrics-logging.md`.\n",
