            "content": "# CLI (droid)\n\n`apps/cli` is the Droid CLI — the primary runtime for the AI agent. It runs either as a full-screen interactive terminal UI or in headless exec mode for scripted use.\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe CLI is where the agent loop lives. It receives messages from the user (via TUI or stdin), sends them to an LLM, interprets the model's tool calls, confirms or executes those tools, and streams the results back. All agent logic, tool execution, and streaming happens inside this process.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/cli/src/\n├── index.ts                    # Entry point — detects mode, initializes env and auth\n├── app.tsx                     # Root TUI component (Ink/React)\n├── main.tsx                    # TUI renderer entry\n├── commands/                   # All CLI commands (exec, wiki-upload, login, etc.)\n│   ├── exec.ts                 # `droid exec` command (headless mode)\n│   ├── wiki-upload.ts          # `droid wiki-upload` command\n│   └── ...\n├── exec/                       # Exec runners (agent loop implementations)\n│   ├── streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts   # Main exec runner (daemon-connected)\n│   ├── renderlessExecRunner.ts         # Renderless exec runner (no TUI)\n│   ├── sharedAgentRunner.ts            # Shared logic between runners\n│   └── ...\n├── agent/                      # Agent behavior (tool confirmation, permissions)\n│   ├── tool-confirmation.ts\n│   ├── tools.ts\n│   └── ...\n├── components/                 # TUI React/Ink components\n├── services/                   # Local services (session, settings, auth)\n├── hooks/                      # React hooks for TUI state\n├── controllers/                # Session and state controllers\n├── acp/                        # Agent Command Protocol handlers\n├── mcp/                        # MCP server integration\n└── utils/                      # CLI utilities\n```\n\n## Modes of operation\n\n### Interactive TUI mode\n\nDefault when no subcommand is provided. Renders a full-screen Ink/React interface (`app.tsx`) with a chat window, tool confirmation dialogs, session list, and settings panels.\n\n```bash\ndroid           # launches TUI\ndroid-dev       # dev alias pointing to hosted dev environment\ndroid-localhost # dev alias pointing to local API\n```\n\n### Exec mode (headless)\n\nInvoked with the `exec` subcommand. Runs the agent loop without a TUI, writing structured output (JSON or plain text) to stdout. Used for CI pipelines and programmatic use.\n\n```bash\ndroid exec --prompt \"Add unit tests to src/auth.ts\"\ndroid exec --prompt \"...\" --output-format json\n```\n\nThe exec runner is `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` (when connected to daemon) or `apps/cli/src/exec/renderlessExecRunner.ts` (standalone).\n\n## Key files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/index.ts` | Entry point, mode detection, env/auth init |\n| `apps/cli/src/app.tsx` | Root TUI React component (161k lines, core UI) |\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/exec.ts` | `droid exec` command handler (60k lines) |\n| `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` | Main agent loop, daemon-connected |\n| `apps/cli/src/exec/renderlessExecRunner.ts` | Headless exec runner |\n| `apps/cli/src/agent/tools.ts` | Tool selection and execution |\n| `apps/cli/src/agent/tool-confirmation.ts` | Tool permission logic |\n\n## Build\n\nThe CLI compiles to a Single Executable Application (SEA) using Bun and Node.js SEA API:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run build      # builds for current platform\ncd apps/cli && npm run bundle     # produces bundled JS (before SEA packaging)\n```\n\nThe build process is in `apps/cli/esbuild.config.js`. Supported targets: macOS ARM64/x64, Linux ARM64/x64, Windows x64.\n\n## See also\n\n- [Command structure](command-structure.md)\n- [TUI rendering](tui-rendering.md)\n- [Exec mode](exec-mode.md)\n- [Agent execution feature](../../features/agent-execution/index.md)\n",
