            "content": "# CLI command structure\n\nThe CLI has two top-level modes: interactive TUI (default) and Commander-based subcommands. The entry point at `apps/cli/src/index.ts` detects which mode to use based on the arguments provided.\n\n## Mode detection\n\n```typescript\n// apps/cli/src/index.ts\n// No positional args → Interactive TUI\n// Any subcommand → Commander\n```\n\nWhen launched without arguments, the CLI renders the Ink TUI. When any recognized subcommand is provided, Commander parses and dispatches it.\n\n## Subcommands\n\nThe subcommands are registered in `apps/cli/src/commands/index.ts` and implemented as individual files in `apps/cli/src/commands/`.\n\n### Core subcommands\n\n| Command | File | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `exec` | `commands/exec.ts` | Headless agent execution |\n| `wiki-upload` | `commands/wiki-upload.ts` | Upload wiki to Factory |\n| `login` | `commands/loginCommand.ts` | Authenticate with Factory |\n| `logout` | `commands/logoutCommand.ts` | Sign out |\n| `new` | `commands/new.ts` | Start a new session |\n| `sessions` | `commands/sessions.ts` | List and manage sessions |\n\n### Session management\n\n| Command | File | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `fork` | `commands/fork.ts` | Fork current session |\n| `rewind` | `commands/rewind.ts` | Rewind session to a checkpoint |\n| `compact` | `commands/compact.ts` | Compact conversation history |\n| `rename` | `commands/rename.ts` | Rename a session |\n| `clear` | `commands/clear.ts` | Clear session |\n| `share` | `commands/share.ts` | Share session link |\n\n### Configuration\n\n| Command | File | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `settings` | `commands/settings.ts` | View/edit settings |\n| `model` | `commands/model.ts` | Select LLM model |\n| `language` | `commands/language.ts` | Set response language |\n| `hooks` | `commands/hooks.ts` | Manage lifecycle hooks |\n\n### Integration commands\n\n| Command | File | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `ssh` | `commands/ssh.ts` | SSH into a CDE |\n| `ide` | `commands/ide.ts` | Connect IDE extension |\n| `mcp` | `commands/mcp/` | Manage MCP servers |\n| `plugin` | `commands/plugin/` | Manage plugins |\n| `skills` | `commands/skills/` | Manage skills |\n\n### Mission commands\n\n| Command | File | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `enter-mission` | `commands/enter-mission.ts` | Enter mission mode |\n| `exit-mission` | `commands/exit-mission.ts` | Exit mission mode |\n| `missions` | `commands/missions.ts` | List missions |\n\n### Operational commands\n\n| Command | File | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `update` | `commands/update.ts` | Update the CLI |\n| `bug` | `commands/bug.ts` | Submit a bug report |\n| `diagnostics` | `commands/diagnostics.ts` | Show diagnostic info |\n| `status` | `commands/status.ts` | Show daemon status |\n| `daemon` | `commands/daemon.ts` | Daemon control |\n\n## The `exec` command\n\nThe `exec` command is the most complex subcommand. It accepts a prompt and runs the agent loop non-interactively:\n\n```bash\ndroid exec --prompt \"Add unit tests to auth.ts\"\ndroid exec --prompt \"...\" --model claude-3-5-sonnet\ndroid exec --prompt \"...\" --output-format json --output-file results.json\ndroid exec --prompt \"...\" --autonomy full  # skip all confirmations\n```\n\nKey options:\n\n| Flag | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `--prompt` | The task to execute |\n| `--model` | LLM model to use |\n| `--output-format` | `text` (default) or `json` |\n| `--output-file` | Write output to file |\n| `--autonomy` | Confirmation behavior (`default`, `low`, `medium`, `high`, `full`) |\n| `--tool` | Allow or block specific tools |\n| `--session-id` | Resume an existing session |\n| `--byok` | Bring Your Own Key configuration |\n\n## Command registration\n\nAll commands are registered in `apps/cli/src/commands/index.ts`, which builds a Commander instance and attaches each subcommand. The `app.tsx` TUI handles keyboard shortcuts that trigger the same underlying command logic.\n\n## Validation\n\nOption validation happens in `apps/cli/src/commands/assertValidOptions.ts`, which validates model names, autonomy modes, and tool selections before running the agent.\n",
