            "content": "# Daemon (factoryd)\n\n`apps/daemon` is the Factory daemon — a long-running background process that manages droid sessions, spawns CLI processes, and provides WebSocket-based terminal access.\n\n## Purpose\n\n`factoryd` runs between the user interface (web or desktop) and the Droid CLI processes. It accepts connections over WebSocket, spawns one CLI process per session, and routes messages between the UI and the CLI over stdin/stdout. It also manages raw terminal sessions for remote command access.\n\nThe daemon runs in two deployment contexts:\n\n1. **Local machine** — bundled inside the desktop Electron app. The desktop app starts and stops the daemon automatically.\n2. **Remote CDE** — downloaded from `downloads.factory.ai` onto E2B cloud sandbox environments during workspace initialization. Auto-updates on startup.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/daemon/src/\n├── index.ts            # Entry point — env init, auto-update, commander, startup\n├── environment.ts      # Environment variable access\n├── constants.ts        # Port numbers and other constants\n├── services/           # UpdateService (auto-update logic)\n├── telemetry/          # OTEL tracing client\n└── utils/              # daemon-telemetry-client, parent-health-monitor, etc.\n\npackages/daemon-core/src/   # Core daemon logic (reused by apps/daemon and apps/cli)\n├── index.ts            # DaemonCore class — main server bootstrap\n├── server/             # WebSocket server, request handlers\n├── droid/              # Droid process management\n├── terminal/           # PTY-based terminal sessions\n├── relay/              # Relay client for remote connections\n├── automations/        # Automation handlers\n└── utils/              # Internal utilities\n```\n\n## WebSocket API\n\nThe daemon exposes a WebSocket server with JSON-RPC 2.0. Default ports:\n\n- `37643` — production\n- `41723` — development\n\nHealth endpoints:\n\n- `GET /health` — uptime and session counts\n- `GET /status` — detailed status with connections and terminal sessions\n\n## Supported operations\n\n### Droid session management\n\n| Method | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `daemon.initialize_session` | Spawn a new droid CLI process for a session |\n| `daemon.load_session` | Load an existing session (reconnect) |\n| `daemon.add_user_message` | Send a message to an active droid process |\n| `daemon.interrupt_session` | Interrupt the agent mid-execution |\n| `daemon.kill_worker_session` | Kill a worker session (missions) |\n| `daemon.update_session_settings` | Update session settings live |\n\n### Terminal management\n\n| Method | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `daemon.create_terminal` | Spawn a new PTY-based terminal session |\n| `daemon.write_terminal_data` | Send input to a terminal |\n| `daemon.resize_terminal` | Resize terminal window |\n| `daemon.close_terminal` | Close a terminal session |\n| `daemon.list_terminals` | List all active terminal sessions |\n\nFor the full protocol, see [JSON-RPC protocol](json-rpc-protocol.md).\n\n## Key files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/daemon/src/index.ts` | Entry point, auto-update, CLI parsing |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/index.ts` | `DaemonCore` class |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/` | WebSocket server, request handlers |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/droid/` | Droid process lifecycle |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/` | PTY terminal management |\n\n## Auto-update\n\nThe daemon checks for updates on every startup. The update check calls `apps/daemon/src/services/UpdateService.ts`, which polls `downloads.factory.ai` for the latest version. If a newer version is found, the daemon downloads and replaces itself before starting.\n\nThis auto-update is disabled when `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=true` (used when bundled with the Electron app, which manages its own update cycle).\n\n## See also\n\n- [Session management](session-management.md)\n- [JSON-RPC protocol](json-rpc-protocol.md)\n- [daemon-core package](../../packages/daemon-core.md)\n",
