            "content": "# JSON-RPC protocol\n\nThe daemon uses JSON-RPC 2.0 for all inter-process communication. Two transport channels:\n\n1. **WebSocket** — between the frontend (web/desktop) and the daemon\n2. **stdin/stdout** — between the daemon and each spawned CLI process\n\nBoth channels use the same JSON-RPC 2.0 wire format. Method names are defined in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`.\n\n## Message format\n\nStandard JSON-RPC 2.0 for requests and responses:\n\n```json\n{ \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"id\": 1, \"method\": \"daemon.initialize_session\", \"params\": { ... } }\n{ \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"id\": 1, \"result\": { ... } }\n{ \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"id\": 1, \"error\": { \"code\": -32000, \"message\": \"...\" } }\n```\n\nNotifications (no `id`):\n\n```json\n{ \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"droid.session_notification\", \"params\": { ... } }\n```\n\n## Methods: frontend → daemon\n\nThese are `DaemonServerMethod` values from `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`:\n\n### Session methods\n\n| Method | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `daemon.initialize_session` | Start a new session, spawn CLI process |\n| `daemon.load_session` | Reconnect to an existing session |\n| `daemon.add_user_message` | Send user message to active session |\n| `daemon.interrupt_session` | Send interrupt signal to CLI |\n| `daemon.kill_worker_session` | Terminate a worker session |\n| `daemon.update_session_settings` | Update model, autonomy, or other settings |\n\n### MCP methods\n\n| Method | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `daemon.toggle_mcp_server` | Enable/disable an MCP server |\n| `daemon.authenticate_mcp_server` | Trigger OAuth for an MCP server |\n| `daemon.add_mcp_server` | Register a new MCP server |\n| `daemon.remove_mcp_server` | Remove an MCP server |\n| `daemon.list_mcp_registry` | List available MCP servers from registry |\n| `daemon.list_mcp_tools` | List tools from connected MCP servers |\n| `daemon.toggle_mcp_tool` | Enable/disable a specific MCP tool |\n\n### Other methods\n\n| Method | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `daemon.list_skills` | List available skills |\n| `daemon.submit_bug_report` | Submit a bug report |\n\n## Methods: daemon → frontend\n\nThese are `DroidClientMethod` values:\n\n| Method | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `droid.session_notification` | Push event from CLI to frontend |\n| `droid.request_permission` | Request tool confirmation from user |\n| `droid.ask_user` | Ask the user a question (AskUser tool) |\n\n## Session notification types\n\nThe `droid.session_notification` method carries a `type` field (a `SessionNotificationType` value) that identifies the event:\n\n| Type | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `create_message` | New message created (user or assistant) |\n| `tool_result` | Tool execution completed with result |\n| `tool_progress_update` | Tool in-progress update |\n| `assistant_text_delta` | Streaming text chunk from assistant |\n| `thinking_text_delta` | Streaming thinking chunk (extended thinking mode) |\n| `droid_working_state_changed` | Agent state changed (idle, executing, etc.) |\n| `session_title_updated` | Session title auto-generated |\n| `session_token_usage_changed` | Token usage counter updated |\n| `settings_updated` | Session settings changed |\n| `permission_resolved` | Previous permission request resolved |\n| `mcp_status_changed` | MCP server connection status changed |\n| `mission_state_changed` | Mission run state changed |\n| `mission_features_changed` | Mission feature list updated |\n| `mission_progress_entry` | Mission progress log entry |\n| `mission_heartbeat` | Heartbeat from mission orchestrator |\n| `mission_worker_started` | Worker session started |\n| `mission_worker_completed` | Worker session completed |\n| `mcp_auth_required` | MCP server needs authentication |\n| `mcp_auth_completed` | MCP OAuth completed |\n| `error` | Error notification |\n\n## Schema validation\n\nAll protocol messages are validated against JSON schemas defined in `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/`. This catches protocol mismatches at the boundary.\n\n## Adding new protocol methods\n\nTo add a new method to the protocol:\n\n1. Add the method name to the appropriate enum in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`\n2. Add the message schema to `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/`\n3. Add a handler in `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/`\n4. Add the handler to the CLI's `streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` if the CLI needs to respond\n5. Add the frontend handler in `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts`\n\nSee [debugging guide](../../how-to-contribute/debugging.md#schema-or-enum-mismatch) for troubleshooting schema mismatches.\n",
