            "content": "# Backend\n\n`apps/backend` is the Factory backend API service — a Next.js 15 application that provides REST endpoints for all platform functionality.\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe backend handles everything that requires server-side execution: authentication, session persistence, LLM proxying, billing, integrations, and webhooks. The web UI portion of this Next.js app is deprecated; `apps/web` is the active web interface.\n\n## Tech stack\n\n- **Next.js 15** with App Router\n- **TypeScript** throughout\n- **Firebase/Firestore** for data persistence\n- **WorkOS** for authentication (`@workos-inc/node`)\n- **Orb** for billing (`orb-billing`)\n- **Statsig** for feature flags (`@statsig/statsig-node-core`)\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/backend/src/\n├── app/\n│   ├── api/                    # All API route handlers (App Router)\n│   │   ├── auth/               # Authentication endpoints\n│   │   ├── billing/            # Subscription and usage billing\n│   │   ├── sessions/           # Session CRUD\n│   │   ├── llm/                # LLM proxy and streaming\n│   │   ├── integrations/       # GitHub, Linear, Slack, etc.\n│   │   ├── organization/       # Org management\n│   │   ├── cron/               # Scheduled background jobs\n│   │   ├── webhooks/           # Incoming webhooks\n│   │   └── _utils/             # Shared API utilities (middleware, metrics)\n├── services/                   # Business logic layer\n│   ├── billing/                # Orb billing integration\n│   ├── computer/               # Computer use / browser automation\n│   ├── e2b/                    # E2B cloud sandbox management\n│   ├── integrations/           # GitHub, Linear, Slack, Segment, etc.\n│   ├── workos/                 # WorkOS auth service\n│   └── ...\n├── features/                   # Feature-specific logic\n│   ├── feature-flags/          # Statsig integration\n│   ├── llm/                    # LLM feature logic\n│   └── ...\n├── constants.ts                # App-wide constants\n├── middleware.ts               # Next.js middleware (auth gating)\n└── instrumentation.ts          # OpenTelemetry setup\n```\n\n## Request lifecycle\n\nEvery API route is wrapped in `handleRouteMiddleware`:\n\n```typescript\nexport async function GET(request: NextRequest) {\n  return handleRouteMiddleware(request, async () => {\n    // route handler\n    return NextResponse.json({ data });\n  });\n}\n```\n\nThe middleware handles:\n\n1. Authentication validation (WorkOS session tokens)\n2. Error formatting — catches `MetaError` and `ResponseErrorXXX` and returns the correct HTTP status\n3. Request logging and metrics\n\nNever build `NextResponse` manually for error cases — throw the appropriate error class and let the middleware format the response.\n\n## Authentication\n\nAuthentication uses WorkOS AuthKit. The `apps/backend/src/middleware.ts` protects all routes under `/api/` by validating session tokens. Public routes and webhook endpoints are explicitly excluded.\n\nSession tokens come from the frontend (cookie-based). The WorkOS SDK verifies them and attaches user/org context to the request.\n\n## Key files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/backend/src/middleware.ts` | Next.js middleware — auth gating |\n| `apps/backend/src/app/api/_utils/` | Route middleware, metrics helpers |\n| `apps/backend/src/services/workos/` | WorkOS auth service |\n| `apps/backend/src/services/billing/` | Orb billing service |\n| `apps/backend/src/services/e2b/` | E2B sandbox management |\n| `apps/backend/src/features/feature-flags/server.ts` | Server-side feature flag evaluation |\n\n## See also\n\n- [API routes](api-routes.md)\n- [Backend services](services.md)\n- [API reference](../../api/index.md)\n",
