            "content": "# Backend API routes\n\nAll API routes are in `apps/backend/src/app/api/` using Next.js 15 App Router conventions. Each subdirectory corresponds to a route segment.\n\n## Route groups\n\n### Authentication (`/api/auth/`)\n\nHandles sign-in, sign-out, and session management via WorkOS AuthKit. The `/api/auth/callback` route completes the OAuth flow.\n\n### Sessions (`/api/sessions/`)\n\nCRUD operations for Droid sessions stored in Firestore. Key endpoints:\n\n- `GET /api/sessions` — list sessions for the current user\n- `POST /api/sessions` — create a new session\n- `GET /api/sessions/:id` — fetch a session\n- `PUT /api/sessions/:id` — update session metadata\n- `DELETE /api/sessions/:id` — delete a session\n\n### LLM (`/api/llm/`)\n\nLLM proxy endpoints. The CLI routes LLM requests through here when not using BYOK:\n\n- `POST /api/llm/complete` — non-streaming completion\n- `POST /api/llm/stream` — streaming completion (Server-Sent Events)\n\nThe LLM route validates the user's entitlements, applies rate limiting, logs usage to Orb, and forwards the request to the appropriate provider (Anthropic, OpenAI, or Google).\n\nSee [LLM proxy](../../api/llm-proxy.md) for more detail.\n\n### Billing (`/api/billing/`)\n\nSubscription and usage management via Orb:\n\n- `GET /api/billing/subscription` — current subscription details\n- `POST /api/billing/checkout` — initiate checkout\n- `GET /api/billing/usage` — usage statistics\n\n### Integrations (`/api/integrations/`)\n\nThird-party integration management:\n\n- GitHub — repository access, OAuth\n- Linear — ticket sync\n- Slack — notifications\n- Jira — ticket access\n\n### Organization (`/api/organization/`)\n\nOrganization CRUD, member management, and settings:\n\n- `GET /api/organization` — current org details\n- `PUT /api/organization` — update org settings\n- `POST /api/organization/members` — invite members\n- `POST /api/organization/settings` — update settings\n\n### Cron (`/api/cron/`)\n\nServer-side scheduled jobs. These endpoints are called by Vercel Cron on a schedule:\n\n- Daily usage rollups\n- Session cleanup\n- Subscription sync with Orb\n- Eval submissions\n\nCron routes are in `apps/backend/src/app/api/cron/`.\n\n### Webhooks (`/api/webhooks/`)\n\nIncoming webhooks from third-party services:\n\n- `POST /api/webhooks/github` — GitHub app events (push, PR, installation)\n- `POST /api/webhooks/workos` — WorkOS user/org events\n- `POST /api/webhooks/orb` — Orb billing events\n\nWebhooks are authenticated via signature verification and are excluded from the standard auth middleware.\n\n### CLI (`/api/cli/`)\n\nEndpoints called directly by the CLI binary:\n\n- `POST /api/cli/login` — exchange auth code for token\n- `GET /api/cli/user` — current user info\n- `GET /api/cli/settings` — fetch user/org settings\n\n### Desktop (`/api/desktop/`)\n\nElectron-specific endpoints for the desktop app:\n\n- `GET /api/desktop/latest-version` — check for desktop updates\n- `POST /api/desktop/download-url` — get S3 presigned URL for update download\n\n### Feature flags (`/api/feature-flags/`)\n\nClient-side feature flag bootstrap — returns the user's feature flag values for the frontend Statsig client initialization.\n\n## Request helpers\n\n`apps/backend/src/app/api/_utils/` contains shared utilities:\n\n- `middleware.ts` — `handleRouteMiddleware` wrapper used by all routes\n- `metrics/` — `fetchWithMetrics`, `callWithMetrics`, `ExternalDependency` enum\n- `firestore.ts` — Firestore client initialization\n\n## Error handling\n\nAll routes throw typed error classes from `@factory/logging/errors`:\n\n```typescript\nthrow new ResponseError404NotFound('Session not found', { sessionId });\nthrow new ResponseError403Forbidden('Org access denied', { orgId });\nthrow new MetaError('Unexpected state', { context });\n```\n\nThe `handleRouteMiddleware` catches these and returns the correct HTTP status code.\n",
