            "content": "# Backend services\n\nThe `apps/backend/src/services/` directory contains the business logic layer. Each service wraps a specific external system or domain.\n\n## Service catalog\n\n### Billing (`services/billing/`)\n\nWraps the [Orb](https://www.withorb.com/) billing platform. Handles subscription creation, usage reporting, plan enforcement, and checkout sessions. The Orb client is initialized from `@factory/services` and configured with the org's subscription tier.\n\nKey operations:\n- Check if an org is within usage limits before allowing LLM calls\n- Report token usage after each LLM response\n- Sync subscription state from Orb webhooks\n\n### E2B (`services/e2b/`)\n\nManages [E2B](https://e2b.dev/) cloud sandbox environments (CDEs). When a user starts a remote session, this service provisions a sandbox, installs the daemon, and returns connection details.\n\n### Computer (`services/computer/`)\n\nBrowser automation via CDP (Chrome DevTools Protocol). Provides computer use capabilities to the agent when the `Computer` tool is invoked — launching browser instances, taking screenshots, and sending input events.\n\n### Integrations (`services/integrations/`)\n\nAll third-party integration services:\n\n| Service | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `github/` | Repository listing, file access, PR operations via GitHub API |\n| `linear/` | Issue sync and ticket management |\n| `slack/` | Notification sending |\n| `segment/` | Analytics event tracking |\n| `exa/` | Web search via Exa API |\n| `loops/` | Email automation via Loops |\n| `stripe/` | Legacy Stripe integration (partially replaced by Orb) |\n| `bigquery/` | Analytics data export |\n| `referrals/` | Referral program tracking |\n\n### WorkOS (`services/workos/`)\n\nAuthentication and identity management via WorkOS. Handles:\n- Session token validation\n- User and org lookups\n- Organization member management\n- SSO/SAML configuration\n\n### Fraud (`services/fraud/`)\n\nFraud detection heuristics applied during account creation and session initialization.\n\n### Remote update (`services/remote-update/`)\n\nManages daemon auto-update on remote CDEs. Called by the admin API and cron jobs to push new daemon versions to remote environments.\n\n### Telemetry (`services/telemetry/`)\n\nInternal telemetry event collection and forwarding.\n\n## Common service patterns\n\nServices use Firestore for persistence. Access Firestore through the centralized client in `apps/backend/src/app/api/_utils/firestore.ts`.\n\nServices wrap external API calls with `callWithMetrics` or `fetchWithMetrics` to get automatic latency tracking and error rate monitoring:\n\n```typescript\nconst result = await callWithMetrics(\n  externalApiCall,\n  ExternalDependency.LINEAR,\n  { labels: { operation: 'get_issue' } },\n  issueId\n);\n```\n\nThis records latency histograms and error counts in Axiom, queryable in the daily metrics dashboard.\n",
