            "content": "# Web app\n\n`apps/web` is the primary web interface for Factory — a Vite + React SPA that provides a browser-based Droid session experience.\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe web app connects to the Factory backend for authentication and data, and to the user's daemon (local or remote) via WebSocket for live droid session management. It renders the same session interface available in the desktop app but in a browser.\n\n## Tech stack\n\n- **Vite** — build tool and dev server\n- **React 19** — UI framework\n- **TypeScript**\n- **WorkOS AuthKit** — browser-based authentication\n\nThe web app is mostly a thin shell that imports the `@factory/frontend` package for all substantial UI functionality. The frontend package handles sessions, settings, authentication state, and most feature logic.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/web/src/\n├── main.tsx        # Entry point, React root\n├── App.tsx         # Root component (minimal)\n├── index.html      # HTML shell\n└── public/         # Static assets\n```\n\n## E2E tests\n\nPlaywright E2E tests for critical user flows are in `apps/web/e2e/`. Run with:\n\n```bash\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e\n```\n\nThe `playwright.config.ts` configures the test runner, base URL, and authentication setup.\n\n## Deployment\n\nThe web app deploys to Vercel. The `vercel.json` configures routing rules for the SPA (all routes serve `index.html`). Deployment happens automatically on merge to `main` via the `deploy-prod-app.yml` GitHub Actions workflow.\n\n## Key files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/web/src/main.tsx` | React entry point |\n| `apps/web/vite.config.ts` | Vite build and dev server configuration |\n| `apps/web/playwright.config.ts` | Playwright E2E configuration |\n\n## See also\n\n- [`@factory/frontend` package](../packages/frontend/index.md) — where the substantive UI logic lives\n- [Sessions feature](../features/agent-execution/index.md)\n",
