            "content": "# Desktop app\n\n`apps/desktop` is the Factory desktop application — an Electron app that wraps the web interface and manages the daemon process locally.\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe desktop app provides a native desktop experience: it bundles `factoryd`, manages its lifecycle, and renders the web interface in an Electron window. It also handles auto-updates for both itself and the bundled daemon.\n\n## Tech stack\n\n- **Electron** with a Vite-based renderer\n- **React 19** (via `@factory/frontend`)\n- **TypeScript** throughout\n\n## Main process\n\nThe Electron main process is in `apps/desktop/src/main/`. Key responsibilities:\n\n- **`initLifecycle.ts`** — app startup, window creation, daemon startup\n- **`factoryd/`** — daemon process management (start, stop, health monitoring)\n- **`ipc.ts`** — IPC handlers for renderer↔main communication\n- **`auth/`** — native credential storage via keychain\n- **`deeplink.ts`** — handles `factory://` deep link URLs\n\n## Renderer process\n\nThe renderer loads the same web interface as `apps/web`. It imports from `@factory/frontend` for session management and UI components.\n\n## IPC communication\n\nThe main and renderer processes communicate over Electron IPC. The preload script at `apps/desktop/src/preload/` exposes a typed IPC API to the renderer. The main process handles IPC requests in `apps/desktop/src/main/ipc.ts`.\n\n## Daemon management\n\nThe desktop app starts `factoryd` on launch and monitors its health. If the daemon crashes, the app restarts it. The daemon binary is bundled in the app's resources directory.\n\nThe daemon is started with `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=true` because the desktop app controls the daemon version via its own update mechanism.\n\n## Auto-update\n\nThe desktop app uses a custom S3-based auto-update mechanism (not Electron's built-in `electron-updater`). The update service in `apps/desktop/src/main/scheduler.ts` checks for new versions on a schedule. Updates are signed and distributed as `.dmg` (macOS) and `.exe`/`.AppImage` (Windows/Linux).\n\n## Build and distribution\n\n```bash\ncd apps/desktop && npm run build    # builds for current platform\n```\n\nPlatform-specific builds are created in CI by the `desktop-build.yml` and `desktop-release.yml` workflows.\n\n## Key files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/desktop/src/main/initLifecycle.ts` | App startup and window management |\n| `apps/desktop/src/main/factoryd/` | Daemon process management |\n| `apps/desktop/src/main/ipc.ts` | IPC handler registration |\n| `apps/desktop/src/main/auth/` | Keychain credential storage |\n| `apps/desktop/src/main/scheduler.ts` | Background update checks |\n",
