            "content": "# @factory/droid-core\n\n`packages/droid-core` is the AI agent core library. It contains tool definitions, LLM provider adapters, message formatting utilities, and streaming infrastructure. The CLI (`apps/cli`) depends on this package for all agent logic.\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/droid-core` abstracts over LLM providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google), defines the tool system the agent uses to interact with the world, and provides streaming utilities for processing model responses in real time.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/droid-core/src/\n├── api/                    # Factory API client (session, droid endpoints)\n├── automations/            # Automation definitions\n├── core/                   # Core agent loop utilities\n├── droids/                 # Droid configuration and types\n├── feature-flags/          # Feature flag checks\n├── llms/                   # LLM integration\n│   ├── provider/\n│   │   ├── anthropic/      # Anthropic (Claude) adapter\n│   │   ├── openai/         # OpenAI (GPT, o-series) adapter\n│   │   └── google/         # Google (Gemini) adapter\n│   ├── errors/             # LLM-specific error types\n│   └── types.ts            # LLM request/response types\n├── machine-connection/     # CDE connection utilities\n├── messages/               # Message creation and formatting\n├── prompts/                # System prompt builders\n├── streaming/              # Streaming response processing\n├── test-utils/             # Testing utilities\n└── tools/                  # Tool system\n    ├── definitions/        # Tool implementations\n    │   ├── cli/            # CLI-specific tools (Execute, Read, Edit, etc.)\n    │   ├── file-tools/     # File operation tools\n    │   ├── mission/        # Mission orchestration tools\n    │   ├── todo/           # TodoWrite tool\n    │   ├── web/            # Web tools (browser, search)\n    │   └── slack/          # Slack tools\n    ├── registry.ts         # Tool registry\n    ├── types.ts            # Tool type definitions\n    └── utils/              # Tool execution utilities\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Type | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| Tool definition | `tools/types.ts` | Interface for a single tool with schema and executor |\n| Tool registry | `tools/registry.ts` | Registers and looks up tools by name |\n| LLM provider | `llms/provider/` | Adapter per LLM provider |\n| StreamingSchema | `streaming/schema.ts` | Zod schema for streaming event types |\n| FactoryDroidMessage | `packages/common/src/sessionV2/` | Message format shared with backend |\n\n## LLM providers\n\nAll three providers implement the same interface but differ in their request/response format. The provider is selected based on the model name:\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    CLI[\"CLI (exec command)\"] --> CORE[\"droid-core LLM layer\"]\n    CORE -->|\"claude-*\"| ANTHRO[\"Anthropic adapter\"]\n    CORE -->|\"gpt-*, o*\"| OPENAI[\"OpenAI adapter\"]\n    CORE -->|\"gemini-*\"| GOOGLE[\"Google adapter\"]\n    ANTHRO --> PROXY[\"Backend LLM proxy\\n(or direct via BYOK)\"]\n    OPENAI --> PROXY\n    GOOGLE --> PROXY\n```\n\nThe `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/docs.md` file documents the expected behavior for adding a new provider.\n\n## Tool system\n\nTools are functions with a JSON schema defining their parameters. The agent requests tool execution, the CLI validates and (if needed) confirms with the user, then executes and returns the result.\n\nSee [tools page](tools.md) for the complete tool catalog and how to add new tools.\n\n## Streaming\n\nThe streaming layer in `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/` handles Server-Sent Events from the LLM proxy and converts them into typed events for the CLI to process. Event types are defined in `streaming/enums.ts` and the full schema in `streaming/schema.ts`.\n\nSee [LLM integration](llm-integration.md) for details on the streaming protocol.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/droid-core/src/tools/definitions/index.ts` | All exported tool definitions |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/tools/registry.ts` | Tool registration and lookup |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/anthropic/` | Anthropic Claude adapter |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/openai/` | OpenAI adapter |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/google/` | Google Gemini adapter |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/schema.ts` | Streaming event schema |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/messages/` | Message creation utilities |\n",
