            "content": "# Tool system\n\nThe tool system in `@factory/droid-core` defines the actions the agent can take. Each tool has a name, a JSON schema describing its parameters, and an executor function.\n\n## Tool catalog\n\n### File tools (`definitions/cli/` and `definitions/file-tools/`)\n\n| Tool | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `Read` | Read file contents, with offset and limit support |\n| `Create` | Create a new file with specified content |\n| `Edit` | Edit a file by finding and replacing text |\n| `MultiEdit` | Make multiple edits to a file in one call |\n| `Glob` | Search for files matching a glob pattern |\n| `Grep` | Search file contents with ripgrep |\n\n### Shell and system tools\n\n| Tool | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `Execute` | Run a shell command (requires confirmation by default) |\n| `LS` | List directory contents |\n\n### Knowledge and web tools (`definitions/web/`)\n\n| Tool | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `WebSearch` | Search the web via Exa |\n| `FetchUrl` | Fetch and parse a URL's content |\n\n### Agent interaction tools\n\n| Tool | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `AskUser` | Ask the user a question with structured options |\n| `ExitSpecMode` | Exit spec mode and present a plan to the user |\n| `TodoWrite` | Maintain a structured todo list |\n\n### Mission tools (`definitions/mission/`)\n\nTools used by the orchestrator and workers in mission mode:\n\n| Tool | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `ProposeMission` | Present a mission plan to the user |\n| `StartMissionRun` | Begin executing the mission |\n| `WorkerCompletionReport` | Worker reports completion to orchestrator |\n\n### Slack tools (`definitions/slack/`)\n\n| Tool | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `SlackPostMessage` | Post a message to Slack |\n| `SlackGetChannelHistory` | Read channel history |\n\n### CLI-specific tools\n\nTools only available inside the TUI/exec context:\n\n| Tool | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `Task` | Spawn a sub-agent to handle a parallel task |\n| `Computer` | Browser automation via Chrome DevTools |\n\n## Tool definition structure\n\n```typescript\n// packages/droid-core/src/tools/types.ts\nexport interface ToolDefinition<TParams, TResult> {\n  name: string;\n  description: string;\n  schema: ZodSchema<TParams>;\n  execute: (params: TParams, context: ToolContext) => Promise<TResult>;\n}\n```\n\nTools are created using the `createTool` helper in `packages/droid-core/src/tools/create-tool.ts`.\n\n## Tool registry\n\nThe registry at `packages/droid-core/src/tools/registry.ts` maps tool names to their definitions. The CLI uses the registry to:\n\n1. Build the tool list to send to the LLM (as JSON schemas)\n2. Look up the executor when the LLM calls a tool\n3. Filter tools based on user settings or `--tool` flags\n\n## Tool confirmation\n\nBefore executing tools with destructive potential, the agent requests confirmation from the user. The confirmation behavior is determined by the `ToolConfirmationType` and the session's autonomy mode.\n\nThe logic lives in `apps/cli/src/agent/tool-confirmation.ts` and `apps/cli/src/agent/shouldConfirmExecution.ts`.\n\n| Tool type | Default behavior |\n|---|---|\n| `Read`, `LS`, `Glob`, `Grep` | No confirmation (read-only) |\n| `Edit`, `Create`, `MultiEdit` | Confirm with diff preview |\n| `Execute` | Confirm with command preview |\n| `AskUser`, `ExitSpecMode` | Always shows to user |\n\n## Adding a new tool\n\n1. Create a file in the appropriate subdirectory of `packages/droid-core/src/tools/definitions/`\n2. Define the tool using `createTool()`\n3. Export from `packages/droid-core/src/tools/definitions/index.ts`\n4. If the tool needs confirmation, add handling in `apps/cli/src/agent/tool-confirmation.ts`\n5. If the tool type is new, add it to `ToolConfirmationType` in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`\n\n## MCP tools\n\nTools from MCP servers are loaded dynamically at runtime and injected into the tool registry alongside the built-in tools. MCP tool management is handled in `apps/cli/src/mcp/`. See [MCP integration](../../features/mcp-integration.md).\n",
