            "content": "# @factory/frontend\n\n`packages/frontend` contains the shared React feature code used by both `apps/web` and `apps/desktop`. This is where the substantial UI logic lives — session management, settings, authentication state, analytics, and most of the feature-level components.\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe frontend package separates reusable feature code from app-specific bootstrapping. Both web and desktop apps import from here rather than duplicating session management, settings panels, or analytics tracking.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/frontend/src/\n├── api/                # HTTP API client wrappers\n├── app/                # App-level providers (Redux store, auth)\n├── auth/               # Authentication state and guards\n├── errors/             # Error boundary components\n├── features/           # Feature-level modules\n│   ├── analytics/      # Usage analytics\n│   ├── automations/    # Automation UI\n│   ├── auth/           # Auth flow UI\n│   ├── banner/         # System banners\n│   ├── debug/          # Dev debug panel\n│   ├── feature-flags/  # Client-side Statsig integration\n│   ├── missions/       # Mission status UI\n│   ├── onboarding/     # Onboarding flows\n│   ├── sessions/       # Session list, management, creation\n│   ├── settings/       # Settings panels (integrations, billing, etc.)\n│   ├── terminal/       # Embedded terminal UI\n│   └── wiki/           # Wiki browser UI\n├── hooks/              # Shared React hooks\n├── layouts/            # Page layout components\n├── router/             # Client-side routing\n├── services/           # Frontend service layer\n│   └── session/        # DaemonSessionController, session state\n├── types/              # Frontend-specific type definitions\n├── utils/              # Frontend utilities\n└── views/              # Page-level components\n```\n\n## State management\n\nThe frontend uses Redux Toolkit with entity adapters. The Redux store is set up in `packages/frontend/src/app/`. Slices follow the pattern of one slice per domain area (sessions, settings, analytics, etc.).\n\n**State selection rules:**\n```typescript\n// Always select precisely, never the whole slice\nconst sessionTitle = useSelector((state: RootState) => state.assembly.sessionTitle);\n```\n\n## Session management\n\nThe `DaemonSessionController` (`packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts`) is the central bridge between the WebSocket protocol and the React state. It:\n\n1. Connects to the daemon's WebSocket server\n2. Receives `droid.session_notification` notifications and dispatches Redux actions\n3. Handles `droid.request_permission` by rendering confirmation dialogs\n4. Sends `daemon.add_user_message` and `daemon.interrupt_session` requests\n\nSee [session management page](sessions.md) for the full detail.\n\n## Feature flags\n\nClient-side feature flags are handled in `packages/frontend/src/features/feature-flags/`. The Statsig SDK is initialized with the user/org context at app startup. Components use the `useFeatureFlagValue` hook.\n\n## Authentication\n\nAuth state is in `packages/frontend/src/auth/`. WorkOS AuthKit provides session tokens that are included in all API calls. The `AuthGuard` component redirects unauthenticated users to the sign-in page.\n\n## Testing\n\nThe frontend package uses Vitest. Tests need the jsdom environment pragma:\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * @jest-environment jsdom\n */\n```\n\nE2E tests live in `packages/frontend/e2e/` and use Playwright.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | WebSocket↔Redux bridge |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/sessions/` | Session list, session creation |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/settings/` | Settings panels |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/feature-flags/` | Client-side Statsig |\n| `packages/frontend/src/app/` | Redux store, app providers |\n\n## See also\n\n- [Session management detail](sessions.md)\n- [Agent execution feature](../../features/agent-execution/index.md)\n",
