            "content": "# @factory/common\n\n`packages/common` is the shared type, enum, and API contract library. Every cross-boundary data shape — messages exchanged between CLI and daemon, request/response types for the backend API, feature flag definitions — is defined here.\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/common` is the single source of truth for shared contracts. It prevents duplicate type definitions and ensures the frontend, CLI, daemon, and backend all speak the same language.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/common/src/\n├── agent/              # Agent-related types\n├── agentReadiness/     # Agent readiness report types\n├── api/                # API request/response types by service\n│   ├── analytics/\n│   ├── backend/\n│   ├── cli/\n│   ├── daemon/\n│   └── v0/\n├── automations/        # Automation types\n├── billing/            # Billing types\n├── cli/                # CLI-specific enums and types\n├── daemon/             # Daemon configuration and types\n├── desktop/            # Desktop-specific types\n├── documents/          # Document types\n├── droid/              # Droid protocol — the most important part\n│   ├── enums.ts        # All protocol enums (DroidServerMethod, SessionNotificationType, etc.)\n│   ├── types.ts        # Droid session types\n│   ├── schemas/        # Zod schemas for protocol messages\n│   └── index.ts\n├── events/             # Event types\n├── feature-flags/      # Feature flag definitions (FactoryFeatureFlags)\n│   └── constants.ts\n├── images/             # Image/asset types\n├── integrations/       # Integration types (GitHub, Linear, etc.)\n├── llm/                # LLM model types\n├── memory/             # Memory feature types\n├── organization/       # Org types\n├── policy/             # Policy types\n├── relay/              # Relay connection types\n├── repositories/       # Repository types\n├── security/           # Security types\n├── session/            # Session execution types\n├── sessionV2/          # Message format types (FactoryDroidMessage)\n├── settings/           # Settings types\n├── shared/             # Cross-cutting shared types\n├── tags/               # Tag types\n├── terminal/           # Terminal session types\n├── timeline/           # Timeline/history types\n├── tools/              # Tool-related types\n└── workspaces/         # Workspace types\n```\n\n## The droid protocol\n\n`packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` defines all the method names and notification types used in the JSON-RPC protocol between frontend, daemon, and CLI. This is the most referenced file in the package.\n\nAny change to the protocol (new method, new notification type) must start here.\n\n## Feature flag definitions\n\n`packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts` defines all feature flags:\n\n```typescript\nexport const FactoryFeatureFlags = {\n  WikiDashboard: {\n    displayName: 'Wiki Dashboard',\n    statsigName: 'wiki_dashboard',\n    defaultValue: false,\n  },\n  // ...\n};\n```\n\nAdding a new feature flag: edit this file, then use the flag via `useFeatureFlagValue` (frontend) or `featureFlags.checkFlag` (backend).\n\n## API types\n\n`packages/common/src/api/` organizes request/response types by service. New API endpoints need their types here before implementation.\n\n## Key files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` | All protocol method and notification enums |\n| `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/` | Zod schemas for protocol message validation |\n| `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts` | All feature flag definitions |\n| `packages/common/src/sessionV2/` | `FactoryDroidMessage` type |\n| `packages/common/src/api/` | API request/response types |\n",
