            "content": "# @factory/daemon-core\n\n`packages/daemon-core` contains the core daemon logic that both `apps/daemon` and (in limited cases) `apps/cli` depend on. It implements the WebSocket server, session management, and terminal management.\n\n## Purpose\n\nBy separating daemon logic into a shared package, the codebase avoids duplication when the CLI runs in daemon mode (for local-first deployments without a separate factoryd process). `apps/daemon` is a thin entry point that wraps `@factory/daemon-core`.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/daemon-core/src/\n├── index.ts            # DaemonCore class — main entry point\n├── types.ts            # Core types and configuration\n├── constants.ts        # Port numbers and defaults\n├── server/             # WebSocket server\n│   ├── handlers/       # JSON-RPC request handlers per method\n│   └── ...\n├── droid/              # Droid process management\n│   ├── droid-process-manager.ts\n│   └── ...\n├── terminal/           # PTY terminal sessions\n│   ├── terminal-manager.ts\n│   └── ...\n├── relay/              # Relay client for remote connections\n├── automations/        # Automation session management\n├── code-server/        # Code server integration (VS Code in browser)\n└── utils/              # Logging, auth, and other utilities\n```\n\n## DaemonCore\n\nThe `DaemonCore` class in `packages/daemon-core/src/index.ts` is the main entrypoint. It:\n\n1. Creates and starts the WebSocket HTTP server\n2. Initializes the session manager and terminal manager\n3. Registers JSON-RPC request handlers\n4. Sets up relay connections for remote CDE access\n\n```typescript\nconst daemon = new DaemonCore(config);\nawait daemon.start();\n```\n\n## WebSocket server\n\nThe server uses `ws` for WebSocket handling and a custom JSON-RPC 2.0 dispatcher. Each incoming connection is authenticated before being allowed to send requests. The handler dispatch table maps method names to handler functions.\n\n## Terminal management\n\nThe terminal manager in `packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/` creates and manages PTY-based terminal sessions using `node-pty` (or the Bun equivalent). Each terminal session is identified by a UUID and tracked in memory.\n\nTerminal data flows bidirectionally: input from the frontend is written to the PTY's stdin, and PTY output is sent back as WebSocket notifications.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/index.ts` | `DaemonCore` class |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/` | Per-method request handlers |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/droid/` | Droid process lifecycle |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/` | PTY terminal management |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/relay/` | Remote CDE relay client |\n\n## See also\n\n- [Daemon app](../apps/daemon/index.md)\n- [Session management](../apps/daemon/session-management.md)\n",
