            "content": "# Agent execution\n\nAgent execution is the core feature of the Factory platform — the process by which the Droid agent receives a task, reasons about it using an LLM, executes tools, and produces results. It spans the CLI, daemon, droid-core, and frontend packages.\n\n## Overview\n\nWhen a user sends a message, the agent goes through an iterative loop:\n\n1. Format the conversation context and system prompt\n2. Send to the LLM (streaming)\n3. Process the streaming response — text deltas and tool calls\n4. For each tool call: confirm with user (if required), execute, record result\n5. Send the tool results back to the LLM\n6. Repeat until the LLM responds with no tool calls (task complete)\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    USER[\"User message\"] --> FORMAT[\"Format context\\n(system prompt, history, tools)\"]\n    FORMAT --> LLM[\"LLM call\\n(Anthropic / OpenAI / Google)\"]\n    LLM -->|\"text\"| STREAM[\"Stream to frontend\"]\n    LLM -->|\"tool_call\"| CONFIRM[\"Confirm with user?\"]\n    CONFIRM -->|\"yes / auto\"| EXEC[\"Execute tool\"]\n    CONFIRM -->|\"no\"| CANCEL[\"Cancel tool\"]\n    EXEC --> RESULT[\"Record result\"]\n    RESULT --> LLM\n    LLM -->|\"finish\"| DONE[\"Task complete\"]\n```\n\n## Key entry points\n\nThe main runner for sessions connected to the daemon is `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts`. This file orchestrates the full agent loop and handles all JSON-RPC communication with the daemon.\n\nFor standalone exec (without daemon connection), the runner is `apps/cli/src/exec/renderlessExecRunner.ts`.\n\nShared agent logic (prompt building, model calling, result formatting) is in `apps/cli/src/exec/sharedAgentRunner.ts`.\n\n## Sub-pages\n\n- [Tool system](../../packages/droid-core/tools.md)\n- [Tool confirmation](tool-system.md)\n- [Streaming](streaming.md)\n\n## Integration points\n\n| Component | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` | Main agent loop |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/tools/` | Tool definitions and registry |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/llms/` | LLM provider adapters |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/` | SSE stream processing |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/prompts/` | System prompt builders |\n| `apps/cli/src/agent/tools.ts` | Tool selection and execution dispatch |\n| `apps/cli/src/agent/tool-confirmation.ts` | Permission and confirmation logic |\n| `apps/daemon/src/server/handlers/` | Daemon-side message routing |\n| `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | Frontend session state |\n\n## Autonomy modes\n\nThe agent's confirmation behavior is controlled by the session's autonomy mode. Higher autonomy = fewer confirmation prompts. In fully autonomous mode (`full`), the agent executes all tools without asking.\n\nThe autonomy mode is set per session and can be changed mid-session. The CLI encodes it in the tool confirmation logic at `apps/cli/src/agent/shouldConfirmExecution.ts`.\n\n## Compaction\n\nWhen the conversation grows too long to fit in the LLM's context window, the agent triggers compaction. This summarizes the conversation history into a compact form and asks the user to confirm before replacing the full history.\n\nThe compaction logic is in `apps/cli/src/commands/compact.ts`. The `CompactionConfirmation` component in the TUI handles the user confirmation step.\n",
