            "content": "# Tool confirmation and permissions\n\nTool confirmation is the mechanism by which the agent asks the user to review and approve actions before executing them. This is what makes the agent trustworthy — the user stays in control of what gets changed on their system.\n\n## Confirmation flow\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Agent as CLI Agent\n    participant Daemon as factoryd\n    participant Frontend as Web/Desktop\n\n    Agent->>Agent: Decides to call Execute(\"rm -rf tmp/\")\n    Agent->>Daemon: droid.request_permission (JSON-RPC)\n    Daemon->>Frontend: droid.request_permission (WebSocket)\n    Frontend->>Frontend: Renders confirmation dialog\n    Note over Frontend: User sees command, approves or denies\n    Frontend->>Daemon: proceed_once / cancel\n    Daemon->>Agent: proceed_once / cancel (stdin)\n    Agent->>Agent: Executes or skips tool\n```\n\n## What requires confirmation\n\nThe `shouldConfirmExecution` function in `apps/cli/src/agent/shouldConfirmExecution.ts` determines which tools need user approval. The decision depends on:\n\n1. The tool type (`ToolConfirmationType`)\n2. The current autonomy mode\n3. Per-session `proceed_always` decisions made by the user\n\nDefault behavior:\n\n| Tool type | Default |\n|---|---|\n| Read-only (`Read`, `Grep`, `Glob`, `LS`) | No confirmation |\n| File modifications (`Edit`, `Create`, `MultiEdit`) | Confirms with diff |\n| Shell execution (`Execute`) | Confirms with command preview |\n| User-facing (`AskUser`, `ExitSpecMode`) | Always shows |\n| Spec mode proposal | Always shows |\n| Mission actions | Always shows |\n\n## User choices\n\nWhen the confirmation dialog appears, the user can choose:\n\n| Choice | Enum | Behavior |\n|---|---|---|\n| Proceed once | `ProceedOnce` | Execute this time, confirm next time |\n| Always allow | `ProceedAlways` | Execute all future calls of this tool type without confirmation |\n| Auto-run low | `ProceedAutoRunLow` | Auto-approve low-risk tools |\n| Auto-run medium | `ProceedAutoRunMedium` | Auto-approve medium-risk tools |\n| Auto-run high | `ProceedAutoRunHigh` | Auto-approve all tools |\n| Edit | `ProceedEdit` | User edits the command before running |\n| Cancel | `Cancel` | Reject the tool call |\n\n`proceed_always` decisions are stored in session settings and persist for the session lifetime.\n\n## Batch confirmation\n\nThe TUI renders batch confirmation dialogs (`BatchToolConfirmationMessage.tsx`) when the agent requests multiple confirmations at once (common in spec mode). The user can approve or deny the entire batch.\n\n## Spec mode\n\nIn spec mode, the agent presents a structured plan before taking any action. The `ExitSpecMode` tool triggers the `SpecModeConfirmation` dialog, where the user reviews the plan and either approves it (the agent proceeds) or gives feedback (the agent revises).\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/agent/tool-confirmation.ts` | Permission request handler and confirmation logic |\n| `apps/cli/src/agent/shouldConfirmExecution.ts` | Decision function for what needs confirmation |\n| `apps/cli/src/components/BatchToolConfirmationMessage.tsx` | TUI confirmation dialog |\n| `apps/cli/src/components/SpecModeConfirmation.tsx` | Spec mode approval dialog |\n| `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` | `ToolConfirmationType`, `ToolConfirmationOutcome` |\n",
