            "content": "# LLM streaming\n\nThe agent receives LLM responses as a real-time stream of events. Streaming allows the TUI to show text as it's generated and process tool calls as they appear, without waiting for the full response.\n\n## How streaming works\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    LLM[\"LLM API\\n(provider)\"] -->|\"SSE\"| PROXY[\"Backend LLM proxy\"]\n    PROXY -->|\"SSE\"| CLI[\"CLI stream processor\"]\n    CLI -->|\"text_delta notification\"| DAEMON[\"factoryd\"]\n    DAEMON -->|\"WebSocket\"| FRONTEND[\"Frontend\"]\n    FRONTEND -->|\"Append to message\"| UI[\"TUI / Web UI\"]\n```\n\nThe stream flows from the LLM provider, through the Factory backend LLM proxy (which adds usage tracking), to the CLI's stream processor. The CLI converts stream events into JSON-RPC notifications that the daemon forwards to the frontend.\n\n## Stream event types\n\nDefined in `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/enums.ts`:\n\n| Event | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `text` | Text chunk to append to the current message |\n| `thinking` | Extended thinking chunk (reasoning tokens, Claude only) |\n| `tool_call` | Agent wants to call a tool |\n| `tool_result` | Tool execution completed with result |\n| `usage` | Token usage update (input/output counts) |\n| `finish` | Response complete |\n| `error` | Stream error |\n\n## Frontend rendering\n\nText deltas arrive as `assistant_text_delta` notifications. The frontend appends them to the current message in real time, giving the typewriter effect.\n\n`thinking_text_delta` notifications carry reasoning content from models with extended thinking (Claude Sonnet, Claude Opus). The TUI renders this in a collapsible `ThinkingDisplay` component.\n\n## Stream interruption\n\nThe user can interrupt a streaming response at any time. The interrupt flow:\n\n1. User presses the interrupt hotkey or clicks the interrupt button\n2. Frontend sends `daemon.interrupt_session`\n3. Daemon signals the CLI process\n4. CLI stops the current LLM stream and tool execution\n5. Agent returns to idle state\n\nThe CLI handles interruption in the stream processor by checking an interrupt flag before processing each event.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/schema.ts` | Zod schema for all stream event types |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/enums.ts` | Stream event type enum |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/data-stream-parts.ts` | Event part type definitions |\n| `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` | Stream processing and notification dispatch |\n| `apps/cli/src/components/ThinkingDisplay.tsx` | Extended thinking display |\n| `apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/` | Backend LLM proxy (streaming forwarding) |\n",
