            "content": "# Missions (AGI mode)\n\nMissions are Factory's autonomous task decomposition feature. The user specifies a large goal, and an orchestrator agent decomposes it into features, spawns worker sessions to implement each feature, and tracks overall progress — without requiring continuous human oversight.\n\n## Overview\n\nMissions use an orchestrator/worker pattern:\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    USER[\"User goal\"] --> ORCHESTRATOR[\"Orchestrator session\\n(droid CLI)\"]\n    ORCHESTRATOR --> PROPOSE[\"ProposeMission tool\\n(plan presented to user)\"]\n    PROPOSE -->|\"User approves\"| RUN[\"StartMissionRun tool\"]\n    RUN --> WORKER1[\"Worker session 1\\n(Feature A)\"]\n    RUN --> WORKER2[\"Worker session 2\\n(Feature B)\"]\n    RUN --> WORKER3[\"Worker session 3\\n(Feature C)\"]\n    WORKER1 -->|\"Completed\"| ORCHESTRATOR\n    WORKER2 -->|\"Completed\"| ORCHESTRATOR\n    WORKER3 -->|\"Completed\"| ORCHESTRATOR\n    ORCHESTRATOR --> DONE[\"Mission complete\"]\n```\n\n## Mission lifecycle\n\nStates defined in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` (`MissionState`):\n\n| State | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `awaiting_input` | Waiting for user to send the goal |\n| `initializing` | Orchestrator creating mission artifacts |\n| `running` | Workers active, orchestrator monitoring |\n| `paused` | User paused execution |\n| `orchestrator_turn` | Worker returned control, orchestrator acts |\n| `completed` | All features done |\n\n## Feature tracking\n\nFeatures represent sub-tasks within a mission. Each feature has a status (`FeatureStatus`):\n\n- `pending` — not started\n- `in_progress` — assigned to a worker\n- `completed` — done\n- `cancelled` — dropped\n\nFeatures can complete with a success state (`FeatureSuccessState`): `success`, `partial`, or `failure`.\n\n## How sessions coordinate\n\nThe orchestrator and workers are separate CLI processes managed by the daemon. The orchestrator uses mission-specific tools from `packages/droid-core/src/tools/definitions/mission/`:\n\n- `ProposeMission` — presents the decomposition to the user for approval\n- `StartMissionRun` — begins executing features\n\nWorkers use the standard tool set but operate in worker mode with restricted autonomy.\n\nMission progress events flow through the standard session notification channel:\n\n| Notification | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `mission_state_changed` | Overall mission state changed |\n| `mission_features_changed` | Feature list updated |\n| `mission_progress_entry` | Log entry (worker started, completed, etc.) |\n| `mission_heartbeat` | Orchestrator heartbeat |\n| `mission_worker_started` | Worker session began |\n| `mission_worker_completed` | Worker session ended |\n\n## Frontend UI\n\nThe mission control panel in `apps/cli/src/components/mission-control/` shows:\n\n- Overall mission state\n- Feature list with status indicators\n- Progress log\n- Worker status per feature\n\nThe `MissionsList.tsx` component provides a summary view of all missions, and `MissionProposalConfirmation.tsx` renders the plan approval dialog.\n\n## Entering mission mode\n\n```bash\ndroid enter-mission     # switch current session to mission mode\ndroid exit-mission      # return to standard mode\n```\n\nOr from the TUI via the mission mode toggle.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/enter-mission.ts` | Enter mission mode command |\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/exit-mission.ts` | Exit mission mode command |\n| `apps/cli/src/components/mission-control/` | Mission TUI components |\n| `apps/cli/src/components/MissionProposalConfirmation.tsx` | Plan approval dialog |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/tools/definitions/mission/` | Mission orchestration tools |\n| `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` | `MissionState`, `FeatureStatus` enums |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/missions/` | Web/desktop mission UI |\n",
