            "content": "# REST endpoints\n\nThe Factory backend (`apps/backend`) exposes a Next.js 15 App Router API. All routes are under `/api/`.\n\n## Authentication\n\nAll API calls require authentication. WorkOS AuthKit manages sessions via HTTP-only cookies. The `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header is also accepted for programmatic access.\n\nThe Next.js middleware at `apps/backend/src/middleware.ts` validates all requests before they reach route handlers. Unauthenticated requests receive `401 Unauthorized`.\n\n## Session management\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `GET` | `/api/sessions` | List user's sessions |\n| `POST` | `/api/sessions` | Create a new session |\n| `GET` | `/api/sessions/:id` | Get session details |\n| `PUT` | `/api/sessions/:id` | Update session metadata |\n| `DELETE` | `/api/sessions/:id` | Delete a session |\n| `GET` | `/api/sessions/:id/messages` | Get session message history |\n\n## Authentication endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `GET` | `/api/auth/callback` | WorkOS OAuth callback |\n| `GET` | `/api/auth/logout` | Sign out |\n| `GET` | `/api/auth/session` | Current session info |\n\n## LLM proxy\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `POST` | `/api/llm/stream` | Streaming LLM completion (SSE) |\n| `POST` | `/api/llm/complete` | Non-streaming LLM completion |\n\nSee [LLM proxy](llm-proxy.md) for request/response format.\n\n## Organization management\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `GET` | `/api/organization` | Get current org |\n| `PUT` | `/api/organization` | Update org settings |\n| `GET` | `/api/organization/members` | List org members |\n| `POST` | `/api/organization/members` | Invite a member |\n| `DELETE` | `/api/organization/members/:id` | Remove a member |\n\n## Billing\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `GET` | `/api/billing/subscription` | Current subscription |\n| `POST` | `/api/billing/checkout` | Start checkout |\n| `GET` | `/api/billing/usage` | Current usage statistics |\n\n## Integrations\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `GET` | `/api/integrations` | List connected integrations |\n| `POST` | `/api/integrations/github/connect` | Connect GitHub |\n| `DELETE` | `/api/integrations/github/disconnect` | Disconnect GitHub |\n| Similar patterns for Linear, Slack, Jira | | |\n\n## CLI endpoints\n\nUsed by the `droid` binary:\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `POST` | `/api/cli/login` | Exchange auth code for token |\n| `GET` | `/api/cli/user` | Current user info |\n| `GET` | `/api/cli/settings` | User/org settings |\n\n## Webhooks\n\n| Method | Path | Source |\n|---|---|---|\n| `POST` | `/api/webhooks/github` | GitHub app events |\n| `POST` | `/api/webhooks/workos` | WorkOS user/org events |\n| `POST` | `/api/webhooks/orb` | Orb billing events |\n\nWebhooks verify signatures before processing. They are excluded from auth middleware.\n\n## Error responses\n\nAll errors follow a consistent format:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Resource not found\",\n  \"code\": \"NOT_FOUND\",\n  \"statusCode\": 404,\n  \"details\": { \"resourceId\": \"session-abc123\" }\n}\n```\n\nHTTP status codes match the error type — `400`, `401`, `403`, `404`, `409`, `422`, `429`, `500`, `501`, `503`.\n\n## Health check\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `GET` | `/api/health` | Returns `200 OK` if service is up |\n",
