            "content": "# Configuration\n\nConfiguration is managed through environment variables. Each app has its own `.env` hierarchy. Environment variables must be accessed through `@factory/environment`, not `process.env` directly.\n\n## Environment file hierarchy\n\nEach app loads environment files in this order (later files override earlier):\n\n1. `.env` — base values, committed to the repo\n2. `.env.{environment}` — environment-specific overrides (development, staging, production)\n3. `.env.local` — local overrides, git-ignored\n\n## Backend environment variables\n\nKey variables for `apps/backend`:\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_ENV` | Environment name (`development`, `staging`, `production`) |\n| `WORKOS_CLIENT_ID` | WorkOS OAuth client ID |\n| `WORKOS_CLIENT_SECRET` | WorkOS client secret |\n| `WORKOS_WEBHOOK_SECRET` | WorkOS webhook signature secret |\n| `FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID` | Google Cloud Firestore project |\n| `FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY` | Firebase service account key |\n| `FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL` | Firebase service account email |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Anthropic API key for LLM proxy |\n| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | OpenAI API key for LLM proxy |\n| `GOOGLE_API_KEY` | Google API key for LLM proxy |\n| `ORB_API_KEY` | Orb billing API key |\n| `STATSIG_SERVER_SECRET_KEY` | Statsig server-side SDK key |\n| `E2B_API_KEY` | E2B sandbox API key |\n| `GITHUB_APP_ID` | GitHub App ID for integrations |\n| `GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY` | GitHub App private key |\n| `SENTRY_DSN` | Sentry error tracking DSN |\n\n## CLI environment variables\n\nKey variables for `apps/cli`:\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `FACTORY_ENV` | Environment (`development`, `staging`, `production`) |\n| `FACTORY_API_BASE_URL` | Backend API base URL |\n| `FACTORY_APP_BASE_URL` | Web app base URL |\n| `FACTORY_DOWNLOADS_BUCKET` | S3 bucket for binary downloads |\n| `FACTORY_AUTO_UPDATE_ENABLED` | Enable/disable CLI auto-update |\n| `FACTORY_MACHINE_TYPE` | Machine type for CDE identification |\n| `STATSIG_CLIENT_SDK_KEY` | Statsig client-side SDK key |\n\n## Daemon environment variables\n\nKey variables for `apps/daemon`:\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `FACTORY_ENV` | Environment |\n| `FACTORY_API_BASE_URL` | Backend API base URL |\n| `FACTORYD_HOST` | Host the daemon binds to |\n| `FACTORYD_PORT` | Port the daemon listens on |\n| `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE` | Disable auto-update (for bundled desktop use) |\n| `FACTORY_OTEL_ENABLED` | Enable OpenTelemetry tracing |\n\n## Build-time configuration\n\nThe CLI and daemon have build-time configuration injected via `bun build --define`. These are set during CI builds and baked into the binary:\n\n- `__FACTORY_ENV__`\n- `__FACTORY_API_BASE_URL__`\n- `__FACTORY_DEPLOYMENT_ENV__`\n\nFor local development (unbundled via `tsx`/`bun run`), the values come from `.env` files instead.\n\n## Feature flags\n\nFeature flags are not environment variables — they are evaluated at runtime via Statsig. See `docs/feature-flags.md` and [patterns and conventions](../how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md#feature-flags).\n\n## App-level settings\n\nUser and org settings (model preferences, integration config, autonomy defaults) are stored in Firestore, not environment variables. They are fetched via the backend API and cached locally in `~/.factory/settings.json` (dev: `~/.factory-dev/settings.json`).\n",
