            "content": "# Factory monorepo\n\nFactory is an AI software engineering platform. The `droid` CLI tool launches an AI agent that can read, edit, and execute code on the developer's machine. Users interact with sessions through either the CLI directly or through a web/desktop application that connects to a local background service (the daemon).\n\nThe monorepo contains all platform components: the CLI agent, the background daemon, the web and desktop front-ends, the backend API, and the relay service that bridges remote computers to the web UI.\n\n## What it does\n\n- **AI coding assistant** — `droid exec` runs an LLM-powered agent that uses tools (file read/write, shell, search, web browsing) to complete coding tasks\n- **Session management** — sessions are persisted and can be resumed, forked, rewound, or shared\n- **Multi-surface UI** — a Vite/React web app and an Electron desktop app both connect to the local daemon over WebSocket JSON-RPC\n- **Remote execution** — the relay service connects a browser to a daemon running on a remote \"Droid Computer\"\n- **Automations** — scheduled or event-driven droid runs without user interaction\n\n## Major components\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| CLI | `apps/cli` | `droid` binary — interactive TUI and exec mode |\n| Daemon | `apps/daemon` | `factoryd` background service |\n| Web | `apps/web` | Vite + React chat interface |\n| Desktop | `apps/desktop` | Electron wrapper for the web app |\n| Backend | `apps/backend` | Next.js 15 REST API |\n| Relay | `apps/relay` | WebSocket multiplexer for remote computers |\n| Droid Core | `packages/droid-core` | LLM integrations, tool definitions, streaming |\n| Daemon Core | `packages/daemon-core` | Environment-agnostic daemon logic |\n| Frontend | `packages/frontend` | Shared React features |\n| Core UI | `packages/core-ui` | Design system |\n| Common | `packages/common` | Shared types, enums, API contracts |\n\n## Quick navigation\n\n- [Architecture](./architecture.md) — how all the pieces connect\n- [Getting started](./getting-started.md) — build, run, and test the project\n- [Domains](./domains/index.md) — deep dives into each major subsystem\n- [API reference](./api/index.md) — backend REST endpoints\n- [Reference](./reference/index.md) — configuration, data models, packages\n",
