            "content": "# Architecture\n\nThe Factory platform has four main runtime layers: the CLI agent, the daemon, the web/desktop frontend, and the cloud backend. A relay service sits between remote computers and browser clients.\n\n## System overview\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    subgraph \"User machine\"\n        CLI[\"CLI (droid)\"]\n        Daemon[\"Daemon (factoryd)\\nport 37643\"]\n    end\n    subgraph \"Browser / Desktop\"\n        Web[\"Web app\\n(apps/web)\"]\n        Desktop[\"Desktop app\\n(apps/desktop)\"]\n    end\n    subgraph \"Cloud\"\n        Backend[\"Backend API\\n(apps/backend)\\nport 3000\"]\n        Relay[\"Relay\\n(apps/relay)\"]\n        Firebase[\"Firestore\"]\n    end\n    subgraph \"Remote compute\"\n        RemoteDaemon[\"Remote daemon\\n(Droid Computer)\"]\n    end\n\n    Web -->|\"WebSocket JSON-RPC\"| Daemon\n    Desktop -->|\"WebSocket JSON-RPC\"| Daemon\n    Daemon -->|\"stdin/stdout JSON-RPC\"| CLI\n    CLI -->|\"REST\"| Backend\n    Backend -->|\"Firestore reads/writes\"| Firebase\n    Web -->|\"REST\"| Backend\n    RemoteDaemon -->|\"WS agent endpoint\"| Relay\n    Web -->|\"WS client endpoint\"| Relay\n```\n\n## Session data flow\n\nA Droid session starts when the user sends a message from the web/desktop app and ends when the agent completes its task or the user interrupts it.\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant F as Frontend (Web/Desktop)\n    participant D as Daemon (factoryd)\n    participant C as CLI (droid exec)\n    participant B as Backend API\n    participant LLM as LLM Provider\n\n    F->>D: WS JSON-RPC — initialize session\n    D->>C: spawn process, stdin/stdout JSON-RPC\n    F->>D: WS JSON-RPC — user message\n    D->>C: forward message\n    C->>B: POST /api/llm/stream (proxied to LLM)\n    B->>LLM: streaming request\n    LLM-->>B: token stream\n    B-->>C: SSE stream\n    C-->>D: JSON-RPC notifications (text delta, tool calls)\n    D-->>F: forward notifications\n    F->>D: tool result (if approval needed)\n    D->>C: forward tool result\n```\n\n## CLI agent loop\n\nThe agent in `apps/cli/src/exec/exec.ts` runs an asynchronous loop:\n\n1. Send current message context to the LLM via the backend proxy\n2. Stream the response — accumulate text deltas and tool calls\n3. Execute approved tool calls (file read/write, shell, search, web)\n4. Send tool results back to the LLM\n5. Repeat until the LLM returns a final text response with no pending tool calls\n\n```mermaid\nstateDiagram-v2\n    [*] --> Streaming: user message\n    Streaming --> ExecutingTools: tool calls received\n    ExecutingTools --> Streaming: tool results\n    Streaming --> Done: final text, no tools\n    Done --> [*]\n```\n\n## Daemon architecture\n\nThe daemon (`apps/daemon`, built on `packages/daemon-core`) runs as `factoryd` on the user's machine. It owns:\n\n- **WebSocket server** — accepts connections from the web/desktop app (`packages/daemon-core/src/server/web-socket-server.ts`)\n- **Terminal manager** — PTY-based terminal sessions (`packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/terminal-manager.ts`)\n- **Droid registry** — tracks active CLI child processes (`packages/daemon-core/src/droid/droid-registry.ts`)\n- **Relay connection** — optional outbound WebSocket to the relay for remote access (`packages/daemon-core/src/relay/RelayConnection.ts`)\n- **Code server manager** — optional VS Code server proxy (`packages/daemon-core/src/server/code-server-proxy.ts`)\n- **Due-run poller** — checks for scheduled automation runs every 60 seconds\n\n## Relay protocol\n\nThe relay (`apps/relay`) is a Bun WebSocket server deployed on Fly.io. It enables a browser to talk to a daemon running on a \"Droid Computer\" (a remote machine or CDE).\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    Browser -->|\"WS /v0/computer/:id/client\"| Relay\n    Relay -->|\"envelope mux/demux\"| ChannelSession\n    ChannelSession -->|\"WS /v0/computer/:id/agent\"| Daemon\n```\n\nEach `ChannelSession` multiplexes N browser clients onto a single daemon connection using an envelope protocol defined in `packages/common/src/relay`.\n\n## LLM provider routing\n\n`packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/router.ts` selects the API provider (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, xAI) for each request:\n\n1. If retrying after failure, cycle to the next available provider\n2. Check `providerRouting` feature flags in order — first enabled flag wins\n3. Fall back to the first provider in the model's `apiProviders` list\n\nThe backend proxies all LLM traffic through `apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/`, adding auth and rate-limit headers before forwarding to the upstream provider.\n\n## Key design boundaries\n\n- `packages/daemon-core` is environment-agnostic — both `apps/daemon` and `apps/cli` (in daemon mode) import it and provide their own `DaemonCoreConfig`\n- `packages/common` is the single source of truth for JSON-RPC schemas, enums, and API types shared between CLI, daemon, and frontend\n- All UI must use `packages/core-ui` primitives — no raw `<div>`, `<button>`, or `<input>` elements\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [CLI](./domains/cli.md)\n- [Daemon](./domains/daemon.md)\n- [AI agent core](./domains/ai-agent.md)\n- [Frontend](./domains/frontend.md)\n- [Backend](./domains/backend.md)\n",
            "file_path": "/Users/jonathanlucuix-andre/Documents/test-repos/factory-mono/droid-wiki/architecture.md"
          },
          "timestamp": "2026-03-09T15:32:13.513Z"
