            "content": "# CLI\n\nThe `droid` binary (`apps/cli`) is the primary entry point for Factory's AI agent. It runs in two modes: an interactive terminal UI (TUI) built with Ink/React, and a non-interactive exec mode that prints output to stdout.\n\n## Entry point\n\n`apps/cli/src/index.ts` bootstraps the CLI:\n\n1. Loads `.env` and `.env.local`\n2. Configures credential storage (via embedded keytar)\n3. Initializes telemetry\n4. Parses arguments with Commander.js\n5. Dispatches to either interactive mode (Ink renderer) or exec mode (`droid exec`)\n\n## Modes\n\n### Interactive TUI\n\nWhen launched without arguments, `droid` renders a full-screen terminal UI using [Ink](https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink) (React for terminal). The main app component is `apps/cli/src/app.tsx` (~163 KB), which handles session navigation, message rendering, and tool interaction.\n\n### Exec mode (`droid exec`)\n\n`apps/cli/src/commands/exec.ts` implements `droid exec`. It accepts a prompt (from the command line, a file with `--file`, or stdin) and runs the agent non-interactively. Output goes to stdout and stderr.\n\nKey exec options:\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `--model` | LLM model to use (e.g., `claude-sonnet-4-5`) |\n| `--autonomy-mode` | Tool approval mode (`auto`, `supervised`) |\n| `--tools` / `--no-tools` | Enable/disable specific tool groups |\n| `--tag` | Tag the session for filtering |\n| `--output-format` | `text` or `json` |\n| `--file` | Read prompt from file |\n| `--reasoning-effort` | LLM reasoning level (`low`, `medium`, `high`) |\n\n## Agent execution\n\n`apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` is the core execution loop (~55 KB). When the daemon launches the CLI as a child process, this runner:\n\n1. Receives a session initialization payload over stdin (JSON-RPC)\n2. Calls the backend LLM proxy and streams the response\n3. Emits JSON-RPC notifications back to the daemon (text deltas, tool calls, status updates)\n4. Waits for tool results from the daemon (when running in supervised mode)\n5. Loops until the LLM returns a final response\n\n`apps/cli/src/exec/renderlessExecRunner.tsx` handles the direct (non-daemon) exec path, where the CLI calls the LLM directly without a daemon intermediary.\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    User -->|\"droid exec 'task'\"| CLI\n    CLI -->|init payload| StreamingRunner\n    StreamingRunner -->|\"POST /api/llm/stream\"| Backend\n    Backend -->|SSE token stream| StreamingRunner\n    StreamingRunner -->|tool call| ToolExecution\n    ToolExecution -->|result| StreamingRunner\n    StreamingRunner -->|final text| CLI\n    CLI -->|stdout| User\n```\n\n## Commands\n\n`apps/cli/src/commands/` contains one file per command:\n\n| Command | File | Description |\n|---------|------|-------------|\n| `exec` | `exec.ts` | Run agent with a prompt |\n| `new` | `new.ts` | Start a new session |\n| `sessions` | `sessions.ts` | List and manage sessions |\n| `fork` | `fork.ts` | Fork an existing session |\n| `rewind` | `rewind.ts` | Rewind session to a checkpoint |\n| `compact` | `compact.ts` | Compact session messages |\n| `model` | `model.ts` | Select LLM model |\n| `login` / `logout` | `login.ts`, `logoutCommand.ts` | Auth |\n| `ssh` | `ssh.ts` | Connect to remote computer via SSH |\n| `computer` | `computer.ts` | Manage Droid Computers |\n| `mcp` | `mcp/` | MCP server management |\n| `wiki-upload` | `wiki-upload.ts` | Upload wiki documentation |\n| `daemon` | `daemon.ts` | Daemon management |\n| `missions` | `missions.ts` | Autonomous multi-step missions |\n| `enter-mission` / `exit-mission` | `enter-mission.ts`, `exit-mission.ts` | Mission session management |\n| `git-ai` | `git-ai.ts` | AI-assisted git operations |\n| `update` | `update.ts` | Self-update the CLI |\n| `bug` | `bug.ts` | File bug reports |\n| `skills` | `skills.ts` | Manage Droid skills |\n| `settings` | `settings.ts` | Manage settings |\n| `status` | `status.ts` | Show daemon and session status |\n| `cost` | `cost.ts` | Show token/cost usage |\n| `hooks` | `hooks.ts` | Manage lifecycle hooks |\n\n## MCP integration\n\n`apps/cli/src/commands/mcp/` implements the Model Context Protocol. MCP servers expose additional tools to the droid agent. The CLI can add, remove, and list configured MCP servers; `McpService` in `apps/cli/src/services/mcp/McpService.ts` manages connections at runtime.\n\n## Skills\n\nSkills are markdown files in `~/.factory/skills/` (personal) or `.factory/skills/` (project). When a skill is active, its instructions are injected into the system prompt. `apps/cli/src/commands/skills.ts` manages the skill registry.\n\n## Settings\n\n`apps/cli/src/services/SettingsService.ts` reads/writes `~/.factory/settings.json`. Settings include the default model, autonomy mode, tool selections, and custom hooks.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Architecture](../architecture.md) — exec runner's place in the full data flow\n- [AI agent core](./ai-agent.md) — tool definitions and LLM integration used by the runner\n- [Daemon](./daemon.md) — the daemon that spawns CLI processes\n",
