            "content": "# AI agent core\n\n`packages/droid-core` contains the LLM integration, tool definitions, streaming pipeline, and agent execution primitives shared by the CLI and backend.\n\n## Package structure\n\n```\npackages/droid-core/src/\n├── api/          # Factory API client wrappers (sessions, droids)\n├── automations/  # Scheduled and event-driven run logic\n├── droids/       # Droid registry and metadata\n├── feature-flags/# Feature flag integration\n├── llms/         # LLM provider routing and error types\n├── messages/     # Message formatting and conversation management\n├── prompts/      # System prompt construction\n├── streaming/    # SSE streaming parsers and schemas\n└── tools/        # Tool definitions, dispatchers, and registry\n```\n\n## Tools\n\nThe agent interacts with the world through tools. Each tool has a name, a JSON Schema input definition, and an implementation.\n\n`packages/droid-core/src/tools/definitions/cli/` contains the tools available to the droid agent when running in CLI mode:\n\n| Tool | File | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| `Read` | `readCli.ts` | Read file contents with line range support |\n| `LS` | `lsCli.ts` | List directory contents with glob filtering |\n| `Execute` | `executeCli.ts` | Run shell commands with timeout |\n| `Edit` | `editCli.ts` | Find-and-replace edits in files |\n| `Create` | `createCli.ts` | Create new files |\n| `Grep` | `grepSearchCli.ts` | ripgrep-powered content search |\n| `Glob` | `globSearchCli.ts` | Glob pattern file search |\n| `AskUser` | `askUser.ts` | Multiple-choice questions to the user |\n| `ExitSpecMode` | `exitSpecMode.ts` | Exit spec mode and present a plan |\n| `ApplyPatch` | `applyPatchCli.ts` | Apply unified diff patches |\n| `Task` | `taskCli.ts` | Launch subagent (custom droid) |\n| `Skill` | `skillCli.ts` | Invoke a skill |\n| `GenerateDroid` | `generateDroidCli.ts` | Generate a new droid configuration |\n\nAdditional tool groups exist for web browsing (`definitions/web/`), Slack (`definitions/slack/`), and mission-specific operations (`definitions/mission/`).\n\n`packages/droid-core/src/tools/registry.ts` manages tool registration and lookup.\n\n## LLM provider integration\n\n`packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/` contains one subdirectory per provider:\n\n- `anthropic/` — Claude models (claude-opus-4-5, claude-sonnet-4-5, etc.)\n- `openai/` — GPT-4o, o3, o4-mini\n- `google/` — Gemini models\n- `xai/` — Grok models\n\nEach provider implements `LanguageModelV1` (from the Vercel AI SDK pattern) with:\n\n- `complete.ts` — core streaming implementation\n- `chunk-schema.ts` — Zod schema for response chunk validation\n- `settings.ts` — provider-specific config options\n- `types.ts` — provider-specific type definitions\n\n`packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/router.ts` selects the provider for each request:\n\n1. If retrying, cycle to the next available provider in the model's `apiProviders` list\n2. Check `providerRouting` feature flags — first enabled flag wins\n3. Fall back to the first provider in `apiProviders`\n\n## Streaming pipeline\n\n`packages/droid-core/src/streaming/` parses the SSE (Server-Sent Events) stream from the backend LLM proxy:\n\n- `schema.ts` — Zod schemas for all stream event types (text delta, tool call start/delta/complete, usage, finish)\n- `data-stream-parts.ts` — typed event union\n- `enums.ts` — `StreamPartType` enum\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant CLI as CLI runner\n    participant Backend as Backend /api/llm/stream\n    participant Provider as LLM Provider\n\n    CLI->>Backend: POST with messages + tools\n    Backend->>Provider: provider-specific request\n    Provider-->>Backend: SSE chunks\n    Backend-->>CLI: transformed SSE stream\n    CLI->>CLI: parse chunks via streaming/schema.ts\n    CLI->>CLI: accumulate text + tool calls\n    CLI-->>Daemon: JSON-RPC notifications\n```\n\n## Messages\n\n`packages/droid-core/src/messages/` handles conversation history:\n\n- Building message arrays for LLM requests\n- Formatting tool results\n- Managing context window (truncation, compaction)\n\n## Prompts\n\n`packages/droid-core/src/prompts/` constructs system prompts. The base system prompt describes available tools and behavioral guidelines. Skills, custom droids, and user settings augment the base prompt at runtime.\n\n## Automations\n\n`packages/droid-core/src/automations/` contains the logic for scheduled droid runs. The daemon's `DueRunPoller` calls `dispatchAutomationRun` when a scheduled automation is due. Automations are stored in the backend (Firestore) and fetched by the daemon.\n\n## Adding a new LLM model\n\n1. Create provider files in `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/<provider>/` (or add to an existing provider)\n2. Register the model in `packages/common/src/llm/` (model constants and `apiProviders` list)\n3. Add a provider mapping in the backend LLM proxy (`apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/`)\n4. Write unit tests in the provider's `tests/` directory using mocks from `test-utils/mocks.ts`\n\nSee `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/docs.md` for the full contributor guide.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [CLI](./cli.md) — the exec runner that calls these tools\n- [Backend API — LLM](../api/llm.md) — the proxy endpoint that forwards LLM requests\n- [Architecture](../architecture.md) — how streaming flows through the system\n",
