            "content": "# Frontend\n\nThe Factory frontend is split across three locations:\n\n- `apps/web` — Vite + React web application (port 3002)\n- `apps/desktop` — Electron desktop app wrapping `apps/web`\n- `packages/frontend` — shared features, hooks, services, and state management\n\nBoth `apps/web` and `apps/desktop` consume `packages/frontend` for all shared logic.\n\n## Web app (`apps/web`)\n\n`apps/web/src/main.tsx` bootstraps the app: mounts the React root, sets up WorkOS AuthKit authentication, and provides the Redux store and router.\n\nAuthentication uses [@workos-inc/authkit-react](https://workos.com/docs). The `apps/web/src/auth/` directory contains auth state management and route guards.\n\n## Desktop app (`apps/desktop`)\n\n`apps/desktop` is an Electron application. It bundles the web app for local rendering and manages the `factoryd` daemon lifecycle:\n\n- On startup, it spawns the daemon process bundled with the app\n- On shutdown or restart, it tears down the daemon\n- Auto-update uses an S3-based distribution (see `packages/updater`)\n\nThe main process (`apps/desktop/src/main/`) handles native OS integration: file system access, tray icon, window management, and IPC bridges to the renderer.\n\n## Shared frontend package (`packages/frontend`)\n\n`packages/frontend/src/` is organized into:\n\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `features/` | Self-contained feature modules (sessions, settings, auth, missions, etc.) |\n| `services/` | Service singletons (DaemonSessionController, telemetry) |\n| `api/` | Typed fetch wrappers for backend REST endpoints |\n| `auth/` | Authentication utilities |\n| `router/` | Route definitions and navigation helpers |\n| `layouts/` | Page layout components |\n| `views/` | Top-level view components |\n| `hooks/` | Shared React hooks |\n| `types/` | Shared TypeScript types |\n\n### DaemonSessionController\n\n`packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` (~81 KB) is the most complex service in the frontend. It manages the WebSocket connection to the daemon and translates JSON-RPC messages into Redux state updates.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n- Connect to the daemon WebSocket (local or remote via relay)\n- Initialize and tear down droid sessions\n- Forward user messages to the daemon\n- Handle notifications from the CLI (text deltas, tool calls, status changes)\n- Dispatch tool results when the user approves/rejects tool calls\n- Manage reconnection on disconnect\n\n### Features\n\n`packages/frontend/src/features/` contains domain-specific modules:\n\n| Feature | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `sessions/` | Session list, session view, message thread rendering |\n| `settings/` | User settings, model selection, tool configuration |\n| `missions/` | Multi-step autonomous mission UI |\n| `auth/` | Login, logout, org switching |\n| `onboarding/` | New user onboarding flow |\n| `automations/` | Scheduled automation management |\n| `analytics/` | Usage analytics and session metrics |\n| `wiki/` | Wiki viewer (in-app documentation) |\n| `terminal/` | Embedded terminal (PTY via daemon) |\n| `feature-flags/` | Statsig integration, `useFeatureFlagValue` hook |\n\n## Design system (`packages/core-ui`)\n\nAll UI must use `@factory/core-ui` components. Direct use of `<div>`, `<button>`, `<input>`, etc. is forbidden. Key primitives:\n\n| Component | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `Box`, `Flex`, `Grid` | Layout primitives |\n| `Button` | All button variants |\n| `Input`, `Dropdown` | Form controls |\n| `Header`, `Text` | Typography |\n| `Collapsible` | Expandable sections |\n| `Toast` | Notification toasts |\n\nColors use a semantic system (`colors.semantics`) with light/dark mode support. Never hardcode hex colors.\n\n## State management\n\nRedux Toolkit with entity adapters. Key conventions from `docs/frontend.md`:\n\n- Select state precisely — `state.assembly.messageTree` not the whole `assembly` slice\n- Components should be stateless when possible\n- CSS-driven interactions over component state for animations and show/hide\n- Maximum 200–300 lines per component; extract longer logic to hooks or subcomponents\n\n## Feature flags\n\nFeature flags use Statsig. In React components:\n\n```typescript\nimport { useFeatureFlagValue } from '@/featureFlags';\nimport { FactoryFeatureFlags } from '@factory/common/feature-flags';\n\nconst isEnabled = useFeatureFlagValue(FactoryFeatureFlags.MyFlag);\n```\n\nFlag definitions live in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`. New flags must first be created in the Statsig console, then added to `FactoryFeatureFlags`.\n\n## Testing\n\nFrontend unit tests use Jest + jsdom. Add `/** @jest-environment jsdom */` at the top of test files that render components.\n\nE2E tests use Playwright:\n\n```bash\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e -- --headed --debug\n```\n\nSee `docs/playwright-e2e-testing.md` for E2E testing conventions.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Architecture](../architecture.md) — WebSocket connection between frontend and daemon\n- [Daemon](./daemon.md) — the daemon the frontend connects to\n- [Reference — configuration](../reference/configuration.md) — frontend environment variables\n",
