            "content": "# Backend\n\n`apps/backend` is a Next.js 15 application running on port 3000. It serves REST API endpoints for the Factory platform. The original web UI in this app is deprecated — all frontend work goes in `apps/web`.\n\n## Structure\n\n```\napps/backend/src/\n├── app/\n│   ├── api/          # Next.js App Router API routes\n│   └── cli/          # CLI-specific endpoints\n├── services/         # Business logic and external service clients\n├── features/         # Feature modules (LLM proxy, feature flags, etc.)\n├── middleware.ts     # Auth and routing middleware\n├── routes.ts         # Route constant definitions\n├── instrumentation.ts # OpenTelemetry setup\n└── constants.ts      # App-wide constants\n```\n\n## API routes\n\n`apps/backend/src/app/api/` has one directory per resource group:\n\n| Route group | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `auth/` | WorkOS authentication callbacks and session management |\n| `sessions/` | Droid session CRUD and message history |\n| `billing/` | Subscription, plan, and usage management |\n| `llm/` | LLM proxy — streams requests to Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, xAI |\n| `integrations/` | GitHub, Linear, Slack, and other third-party integrations |\n| `organization/` | Org settings, members, invites |\n| `github/` | GitHub OAuth and webhook handling |\n| `tools/` | Tool invocation and approval API |\n| `cron/` | Cron job endpoints |\n| `daemon/` | Daemon registration and heartbeat |\n| `feature-flags/` | Statsig feature flag evaluation |\n| `admin/` | Internal admin endpoints |\n| `desktop/` | Desktop app update distribution |\n| `bug-reports/` | CLI bug report ingestion |\n| `search/` | Session and message search |\n| `health/` | Health check endpoint |\n| `webhooks/` | Inbound webhooks from third-party services |\n| `user/` | User profile management |\n| `workspaces/` | Workspace management |\n\n## LLM proxy\n\n`apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/` proxies LLM requests from the CLI to upstream providers. It:\n\n1. Validates the auth token and org membership\n2. Checks usage limits and billing status\n3. Routes to the appropriate provider (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, xAI)\n4. Streams the response back to the CLI as SSE\n5. Records token usage for billing\n\nThe backend does not run LLM inference itself — it adds auth, rate limiting, and observability, then forwards to provider APIs.\n\n## Services\n\n`apps/backend/src/services/` contains service classes for external dependencies:\n\n| Service | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `billing/` | Orb billing API integration |\n| `computer/` | Droid Computer management (E2B sandboxes, CDEs) |\n| `integrations/` | GitHub, Linear, Slack, JIRA, etc. |\n| `workos/` | WorkOS authentication service |\n| `bigquery/` | Analytics event streaming |\n| `segment/` | Product analytics |\n| `exa/` | Web search via Exa API |\n| `e2b/` | E2B sandbox management |\n| `fraud/` | Fraud detection heuristics |\n\n## Authentication\n\n`apps/backend/src/middleware.ts` authenticates all API requests using WorkOS session tokens. Protected routes check for a valid session cookie or `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header.\n\n`apps/backend/src/app/api/auth/` handles WorkOS OIDC callbacks and token exchange.\n\n## Firestore\n\nThe backend uses Firebase Firestore as its primary database. The `apps/functions/` package contains Firebase Cloud Functions for background tasks and Firestore triggers.\n\nDatabase rules live in `firestore.rules` at the repo root. Indexes are in `firestore.indexes.json`.\n\n## Cron jobs\n\n`apps/backend/src/app/api/cron/` contains time-based tasks:\n\n- Session cleanup and archival\n- Billing period rollover\n- Automation scheduling\n- Usage aggregation\n\nCron jobs are triggered by Vercel Cron (configured in `vercel.json`).\n\n## Error handling\n\nAll errors use the typed error classes from `@factory/logging/errors`:\n\n- `MetaError` — internal 500-class errors\n- `ResponseError400BadRequest`, `ResponseError401Unauthorized`, etc. — HTTP error responses\n\nNever throw the vanilla `Error` class. See `docs/error-handling.md` for full conventions.\n\n## Environment\n\n`apps/backend/src/env/` defines typed environment variable schemas using `@factory/environment`. Backend configuration includes Firebase credentials, WorkOS secrets, LLM API keys, Orb billing keys, and feature flag tokens.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Architecture](../architecture.md) — backend's position in the system\n- [API — sessions](../api/sessions.md) — session management endpoints\n- [API — LLM](../api/llm.md) — LLM proxy endpoint\n- [API — integrations](../api/integrations.md) — third-party integration endpoints\n",
