            "content": "# Sessions API\n\nSession endpoints manage the lifecycle of Droid sessions. Type definitions are in `packages/common/src/api/v0/sessions/`.\n\n## Session object\n\n```typescript\n{\n  sessionId: string;\n  title?: string;\n  status: DroidExecutionStatus;  // \"idle\" | \"running\" | \"interrupted\" | \"completed\" | \"error\"\n  messageCount: number;\n  createdAt: number;     // Unix ms\n  updatedAt: number;     // Unix ms\n  completedAt?: number;  // Unix ms\n  templateId?: string;   // Cloud machine template ID\n  machineId?: string;    // Connected machine ID\n  sessionSettings?: SessionSettings;\n}\n```\n\n## Endpoints\n\n### List sessions\n\n```\nGET /api/sessions\n```\n\nReturns a paginated list of sessions for the authenticated user.\n\n**Response**: `SessionListResponseSchema` — `{ sessions: Session[], pagination: PaginationMeta }`\n\n### Get session\n\n```\nGET /api/sessions/:sessionId\n```\n\nReturns a single session by ID.\n\n### Create session\n\n```\nPOST /api/sessions\n```\n\n**Body** (`CreateSessionRequestSchema`):\n```json\n{\n  \"templateId\": \"template-uuid\",\n  \"sessionSettings\": { ... }\n}\n```\n\nCreates a new session connected to a cloud machine template.\n\n### Update session\n\n```\nPATCH /api/sessions/:sessionId\n```\n\nUpdates session settings. Only `sessionSettings` can be patched.\n\n### Interrupt session\n\n```\nPOST /api/sessions/:sessionId/interrupt\n```\n\nSends an interrupt signal to the running CLI process. Returns `{ status: DroidExecutionStatus }`.\n\n### Session messages\n\n```\nGET /api/sessions/:sessionId/messages\n```\n\nReturns the full message history for a session. Message types are defined in `packages/common/src/api/v0/sessions/messages/`.\n\n## Session settings\n\n`SessionSettings` (defined in `packages/common/src/session/settings.ts`) controls per-session behavior:\n\n- `model` — LLM model identifier\n- `autonomyMode` — `\"auto\"` | `\"supervised\"`\n- `tools` — enabled tool groups\n- `reasoningEffort` — `\"low\"` | `\"medium\"` | `\"high\"`\n\n## Session status lifecycle\n\n```mermaid\nstateDiagram-v2\n    [*] --> idle: created\n    idle --> running: user message received\n    running --> idle: agent response complete\n    running --> interrupted: interrupt signal\n    running --> completed: task marked done\n    running --> error: unrecoverable failure\n    interrupted --> running: resume\n```\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Daemon](../domains/daemon.md) — daemon session lifecycle over WebSocket\n- [CLI](../domains/cli.md) — exec command that drives sessions\n",
