            "content": "# LLM proxy API\n\nThe backend proxies all LLM requests from the CLI through `apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/`. This keeps provider API keys server-side and adds auth, rate limiting, usage tracking, and observability.\n\n## Streaming endpoint\n\n```\nPOST /api/llm/stream\n```\n\nAccepts a model, messages array, and tool definitions. Streams the LLM response as SSE (Server-Sent Events).\n\n**Auth**: `Authorization: Bearer <factory_token>` or session cookie.\n\n**Request body**:\n```json\n{\n  \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5\",\n  \"messages\": [...],\n  \"tools\": [...],\n  \"system\": \"...\",\n  \"maxTokens\": 8192,\n  \"reasoningEffort\": \"medium\"\n}\n```\n\n**Response**: SSE stream of typed events. Event schemas are in `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/schema.ts`.\n\nEvent types:\n- `text_delta` — incremental text token\n- `tool_call_start` — tool invocation begins (name + tool_use_id)\n- `tool_call_delta` — partial JSON input for the tool call\n- `tool_call_complete` — tool call fully received\n- `usage` — token counts (input, output, cache_read, cache_write)\n- `finish` — stream end with finish reason\n\n## Provider routing\n\nThe backend calls `routeModelToProvider()` to determine which upstream provider handles the request:\n\n1. If the request specifies `excludedProviders` (retry path), cycle to the next provider\n2. Check `providerRouting` feature flags from Statsig\n3. Fall back to the first provider in the model's `apiProviders` list\n\nProvider endpoints are configured in `packages/common/src/llm/` model definitions.\n\n## Usage tracking\n\nToken usage is recorded per-request for billing. The Orb billing service (`apps/backend/src/services/orb/`) accumulates usage and bills organizations at their plan rate.\n\n## Error handling\n\n| HTTP status | Meaning |\n|-------------|---------|\n| 400 | Invalid request body or unsupported model |\n| 401 | Missing or invalid auth token |\n| 429 | Rate limit exceeded |\n| 503 | Upstream provider unavailable |\n\nThe CLI retries 503 responses by cycling to the next available provider.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [AI agent core](../domains/ai-agent.md) — streaming parser in the CLI\n- [Backend](../domains/backend.md) — other backend services\n",
