            "content": "# Integrations API\n\nFactory supports connections to external services. Integration endpoints live in `apps/backend/src/app/api/integrations/` and service implementations in `apps/backend/src/services/integrations/`.\n\nShared integration types are in `packages/common/src/integrations/`.\n\n## Supported integrations\n\n| Service | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| GitHub | Repository access, PR and issue data, webhooks |\n| Linear | Issue tracking |\n| Slack | Notifications and bot messages |\n| Jira | Issue tracking |\n| Notion | Document access |\n| Sentry | Error tracking |\n\n## Integration model\n\nEach integration stores an OAuth token or API key tied to an organization. The `IntegrationType` enum is in `packages/common/src/integrations/enums.ts`.\n\nIntegrations are fetched by the droid agent when executing tasks that need external context (e.g., reading a Linear issue before writing code).\n\n## GitHub\n\n`apps/backend/src/app/api/github/` handles GitHub OAuth and webhook events. The backend registers a GitHub App; users install it on their repositories to allow the droid to read/write code.\n\n`apps/backend/src/services/integrations/github.ts` wraps GitHub API calls with auth.\n\n## Webhooks\n\n`apps/backend/src/app/api/webhooks/` receives inbound webhook events from third-party services. Events trigger automation runs or update session state.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Backend](../domains/backend.md) — backend service structure\n",
