            "content": "# Configuration\n\nEnvironment variables are managed through `packages/environment`. Each app registers its own environment provider at startup and calls `getEnvironment()` to access typed values.\n\n## Backend (`apps/backend`)\n\nCreate `apps/backend/.env.local` for local development.\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_ENV` | `\"production\"` or `\"development\"` |\n| `FACTORY_API_BASE_URL` | Self-reference URL for internal API calls |\n| `FACTORY_APP_BASE_URL` | Web app URL |\n| `WORKOS_API_KEY` | WorkOS API key |\n| `WORKOS_CLIENT_ID` | WorkOS client ID |\n| `WORKOS_COOKIE_PASSWORD` | Cookie encryption secret (32+ chars) |\n| `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS` | Path to Firebase service account JSON |\n| `FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID` | Firebase project ID |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Anthropic API key |\n| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | OpenAI API key |\n| `GOOGLE_AI_API_KEY` | Google AI API key |\n| `XAI_API_KEY` | xAI API key |\n| `ORB_API_KEY` | Orb billing API key |\n| `STATSIG_SERVER_SDK_KEY` | Statsig server SDK key |\n| `GITHUB_APP_ID` | GitHub App ID |\n| `GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY` | GitHub App private key |\n\n## Daemon (`apps/daemon`)\n\nCreate `apps/daemon/.env.local` for local development.\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `FACTORY_ENV` | `\"production\"` \\| `\"development\"` \\| `\"test\"` |\n| `FACTORY_API_BASE_URL` | Backend API URL |\n| `FACTORY_DEPLOYMENT_ENV` | Deployment environment label |\n| `FACTORYD_HOST` | Host to bind the WebSocket server |\n| `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE` | `\"true\"` to skip update checks |\n| `FACTORY_OTEL_ENABLED` | `\"true\"` to enable OTEL tracing |\n\nBuild-time defines (injected by `scripts/build-sea.ts` during production builds):\n\n| Define | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `__FACTORY_ENV__` | Deployment environment |\n| `__FACTORYD_VERSION__` | Version string |\n| `__FACTORY_API_BASE_URL__` | API base URL |\n\n## CLI (`apps/cli`)\n\nCreate `apps/cli/.env.local` for local development.\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `FACTORY_ENV` | `\"production\"` \\| `\"development\"` |\n| `FACTORY_API_BASE_URL` | Backend API URL (defaults to `https://api.factory.ai`) |\n| `FACTORY_APP_BASE_URL` | Web app URL (used for deep links) |\n| `DROID_EXEC_RUN_TYPE` | Optional label for telemetry (automation exec runs) |\n\n## Relay (`apps/relay`)\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_PORT` | `8080` | Port to bind |\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_HOST` | `0.0.0.0` | Host to bind |\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_DEBUG` | `false` | Enable debug logging |\n\n## Web app (`apps/web`)\n\nThe web app uses Vite environment variables (prefix `VITE_`).\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `VITE_FACTORY_API_BASE_URL` | Backend API URL |\n| `VITE_WORKOS_CLIENT_ID` | WorkOS client ID for AuthKit |\n| `VITE_STATSIG_CLIENT_SDK_KEY` | Statsig client SDK key |\n\n## Ports\n\n| App | Default port |\n|-----|-------------|\n| Backend | 3000 |\n| Admin | 3001 |\n| Web | 3002 |\n| Daemon (prod) | 37643 |\n| Daemon (dev) | 41723 |\n| Relay | 8080 |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Getting started](../getting-started.md) — how to set up a local dev environment\n",
