            "content": "# Data models\n\nKey TypeScript types and shared enums are in `packages/common/src/`. This package is the single source of truth for types shared between the frontend, backend, CLI, and daemon.\n\n## Session\n\nDefined in `packages/common/src/session/enums.ts` and `packages/common/src/api/v0/sessions/schemas.ts`.\n\n```typescript\n// Execution state of a running droid\nenum DroidExecutionStatus {\n  Idle = 'idle',\n  Pending = 'pending',\n  Running = 'running',\n}\n\n// Online/offline connectivity state\nenum SessionStatus {\n  Online = 'online',\n  Offline = 'offline',\n}\n\n// Privacy controls\nenum SessionPrivacyLevel {\n  Private = 'private',\n  Organization = 'organization',\n}\n```\n\nThe `Session` object (REST API shape):\n\n```typescript\n{\n  sessionId: string;\n  title?: string;\n  status: DroidExecutionStatus;\n  messageCount: number;\n  createdAt: number;   // Unix ms\n  updatedAt: number;   // Unix ms\n  completedAt?: number;\n  templateId?: string;\n  machineId?: string;\n  sessionSettings?: SessionSettings;\n}\n```\n\n## Messages\n\nSession messages follow a multi-content-block format defined in `packages/common/src/sessionV2/`:\n\n```typescript\nenum MessageRole {\n  User = 'user',\n  Assistant = 'assistant',\n  Tool = 'tool',\n}\n\nenum MessageContentBlockType {\n  Text = 'text',\n  ToolUse = 'tool_use',\n  ToolResult = 'tool_result',\n  Thinking = 'thinking',\n}\n```\n\n## Daemon JSON-RPC protocol\n\n`packages/common/src/daemon/types.ts` (~862 lines) defines all JSON-RPC method schemas for daemon↔frontend communication using Zod. Key method groups:\n\n| Namespace | Methods |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `droid/*` | `initializeSession`, `loadSession`, `addUserMessage`, `interruptSession`, `closeSession`, `updateSessionSettings` |\n| `terminal/*` | `open`, `write`, `resize`, `close` |\n| `auth/*` | `authenticate`, `connectionStatus` |\n| `automations/*` | `list`, `run`, `pause`, `resume`, `create`, `update`, `delete`, `getHistory` |\n| `tools/*` | Tool approval and result submission |\n\nNotification types are enumerated in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` as `SessionNotificationType`. New notifications require adding an entry here and a corresponding Zod schema in `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/`.\n\n## LLM models\n\nModel definitions are in `packages/common/src/llm/`. Each model specifies:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  id: LLMModel;\n  displayName: string;\n  apiProviders: ApiProvider[];     // Ordered list; first is default\n  maxContextTokens: number;\n  supportsThinking?: boolean;\n  reasoningEffort?: ReasoningEffort[];\n}\n```\n\n`ApiProvider` enum values: `Anthropic`, `OpenAI`, `Google`, `XAI`.\n\n## Integrations\n\nIntegration types are in `packages/common/src/integrations/enums.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nenum IntegrationType {\n  GitHub = 'github',\n  Linear = 'linear',\n  Slack = 'slack',\n  Jira = 'jira',\n  Notion = 'notion',\n  Sentry = 'sentry',\n}\n```\n\n## Automations\n\nAutomation schedule and trigger types are in `packages/common/src/automations/`.\n\n## API type convention\n\nAll API request/response types must be defined in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts`. Use Zod schemas for runtime validation; export TypeScript types via `z.infer<>`. Never define API types inline in backend route handlers.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [API — sessions](../api/sessions.md) — session endpoint shapes\n- [Daemon](../domains/daemon.md) — JSON-RPC protocol usage\n- [AI agent core](../domains/ai-agent.md) — LLM model registry\n",
