            "content": "# Packages reference\n\nAll shared libraries live in `packages/`. Each is an npm workspace with its own `package.json`.\n\n## Core packages\n\n### `@factory/core-ui` (`packages/core-ui`)\n\nDesign system — **mandatory for all UI work**. Provides layout primitives (`Box`, `Flex`, `Grid`), form components (`Button`, `Input`, `Dropdown`), typography (`Header`, `Text`), and interactive components (`Collapsible`, `Toast`). Uses a semantic color system with light/dark mode. Never use raw HTML elements or hardcode colors.\n\n### `@factory/frontend` (`packages/frontend`)\n\nShared React features, hooks, services, and Redux state for `apps/web` and `apps/desktop`. Contains `DaemonSessionController`, feature-specific modules, API wrappers, and routing utilities.\n\n### `@factory/droid-core` (`packages/droid-core`)\n\nAI agent core. LLM provider integrations (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, xAI), tool definitions, streaming parsers, message formatting, and automation dispatch. Used by both the CLI exec runner and the backend.\n\n### `@factory/daemon-core` (`packages/daemon-core`)\n\nEnvironment-agnostic daemon implementation. Both `apps/daemon` and `apps/cli` (daemon mode) import this package. Contains the WebSocket server, terminal manager, droid registry, relay connection, and automation scheduler.\n\n### `@factory/common` (`packages/common`)\n\nShared types, enums, Zod schemas, and API contracts. The single source of truth for anything used across frontend, backend, CLI, and daemon. Organized by domain under `src/`.\n\n### `@factory/services` (`packages/services`)\n\nService layer with business logic and external service integrations shared across apps.\n\n### `@factory/models` (`packages/models`)\n\nTypeScript type definitions and data model schemas for the platform domain objects.\n\n## Utility packages\n\n### `@factory/utils` (`packages/utils`)\n\nGeneral-purpose utility functions (string, date, file system, shell helpers, LLM utilities).\n\n### `@factory/logging` (`packages/logging`)\n\nCentralized logging: `logInfo`, `logWarn`, `logException`. Error classes: `MetaError`, `ResponseError400BadRequest`, etc. OTEL tracing support via `OtelTracing`.\n\n### `@factory/environment` (`packages/environment`)\n\nTyped environment variable provider. Each app registers its own provider and calls `getEnvironment()` to read typed values. Avoids direct `process.env` access.\n\n### `@factory/updater` (`packages/updater`)\n\nVersion checking and auto-update logic for the CLI and daemon. Handles downloading, verifying, and installing new binary releases.\n\n### `@factory/runtime` (`packages/runtime`)\n\nRuntime utilities: credential storage (via keytar), authentication token management.\n\n### `@factory/daemon-client` (`packages/daemon-client`)\n\nTyped WebSocket client for communicating with `factoryd`. Used by the frontend.\n\n### `@factory/signal-core` (`packages/signal-core`)\n\nSignal processing utilities for the daemon's signal app integration.\n\n## Development packages\n\n### `@factory/eslint-config` (`packages/eslint-config`)\n\nShared ESLint rules. Enforces: enums in `enums.ts`, types in `types.ts`, API types in `packages/common`, absolute imports, no `require()`, no direct `process.env` access, no raw HTML elements in UI code.\n\n### `@factory/test-utils` (`packages/test-utils`)\n\nShared test helpers, mocks, and fixtures used across packages.\n\n## Apps\n\n| App | Package name | Description |\n|-----|-------------|-------------|\n| `apps/backend` | `backend` | Next.js 15 REST API |\n| `apps/web` | `web` | Vite + React web app |\n| `apps/desktop` | `desktop` | Electron desktop app |\n| `apps/daemon` | `daemon` | `factoryd` background service |\n| `apps/cli` | `cli` | `droid` CLI tool |\n| `apps/relay` | `@factory/relay` | WebSocket relay |\n| `apps/admin` | `admin` | Admin dashboard |\n| `apps/functions` | `functions` | Firebase Cloud Functions |\n| `apps/storybook` | `storybook` | Component story browser |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Architecture](../architecture.md) — how packages fit together at runtime\n- [Getting started](../getting-started.md) — workspace build and test commands\n",
